title: quiche lorraine(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook bacon in large skillet over medium heat. When bacon starts to turn brown, add onion. Cook until bacon is crisp; drain. Sprinkle cheese into bottom of pie shell. Top with bacon mixture. Combine milk, eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg in small bowl until blended. Pour into pie shell. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Let cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: salmon puff
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, milk and soup.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until mixture appears set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: betty beaman salad
directions: Dissolve 1 box lemon and lime Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water. Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and pour in mold to jell.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in a covered dry container.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Mix pudding according to box directions. Then add Cool Whip. Layer pudding mixture on bottom of
a 9 x 13 pan, then lay graham cracker sheets, then pudding. Keep layering until ingredients are gone. Crumble graham crackers on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: amy's lemon pie
directions: Mix (fold) Cool Whip and thawed lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: spoon bread
directions: Cook the cornmeal and milk until the consistency of mush. Remove from heat. Add the salt, baking powder, oil and milk.
Add the egg yolks. Fold in the egg whites. Bake in greased 2-quart casserole in slow oven at 325° for about 1 hour.
Spoon into warm dishes. Top with butter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: icebox pudding
directions: Combine butter, powdered sugar and eggs.
Mix well. Stir in whipped cream, pineapple and walnuts.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with crushed wafers, reserving some for topping.
Fill with pudding. Cover with the reserved crushed wafers.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter until smooth.
Slowly add milk and continue beating.
Fold in Cool Whip until thoroughly blended.
Pour into pie crust and freeze.
May be garnished with chopped peanuts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onion, garlic and green pepper in olive oil. When thoroughly browned, add remaining ingredients. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: under the sea salad
directions: Add the cream cheese to the orange Jell-O, boiling water and marshmallows.
Let cool.
Add the pineapple, cream and mayonnaise. Pour in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put in the refrigerator and let set until firm.

title: barbecued ham
directions: Mix ketchup, brown sugar, water and vinegar.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Add meat and simmer longer.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and spread half the batter in a well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Layer chiles; sprinkle all but 2 cups of cheese over chiles.
Layer with remaining batter, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Partially thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: meat and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bread crumbs, and throw in a casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: double good blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan. Add water and 2 cups fresh blueberries; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to boil and is thickened and clear (mixture will be quite thick). Remove from heat and stir in butter and lemon juice. Cool. Place remaining fresh blueberries in baked pie shell. Top with cooked mixture. Chill. Serve garnished with whipped cream.

title: veggie pizza bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 for 10-13 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix softened cream cheese with mayonnaise and ranch dressing mix.
Spread onto cooled crust. Sprinkle the veggies on top of the cream cheese mixture and top with cheese.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: low-fat easy skillet meal
directions: Combine meat, crackers, onion, 1 teaspoon ginger, garlic, egg and 1/2 cup water.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
Cook 10 minutes in hot oil in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients except cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water.
Mix them together then add to skillet. Stir until mixture boils.
Return meatballs to skillet.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice, if desired. If beef is used, use beef broth.
Yields six 1-cup servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Line electric skillet with heavy foil and preheat to 375°. Mix first 4 ingredients and cook and stir occasionally until golden brown. Add soda and stir vigorously. Add peanuts and continue stirring until medium brown. Remove foil from skillet. When cool, remove candy from foil.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Stir until mixture becomes one large ball.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove and let cool, then serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water until tender. Drain and pull meat off bones in small pieces.
Save broth.
Melt margarine and pour over crumbs. In square dish, put thin layer of crumbs, then layer of chicken. Empty both soups into bowl. Add 1 soup can of broth. Blend together.
Pour half of the soup over layer of chicken atop this.
Pour remaining soup mixture over this second layer.
Add another layer of chicken and crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: diet strawberry pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup cold water and cornstarch; set aside.
Mix and bring to a boil 1 1/2 cups water and 2 teaspoons Sweet 'N Low.
Add cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick.
Reduce heat to medium and stir in gelatin until blended.
While mixture is hot, add 3/4 cup very cold water.
Cover.
Chill.
Then add sliced strawberries and fill crust.
Let set.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend butter and cheese.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika; mix well.
Cover each olive with 1 teaspoon of the mixture. Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.
Bake in oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: linzer augen cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar.
Beat in egg and extracts.
Add flour and salt.
Chill.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with 1 3/4-inch round cutter.
Cut 2 dozen round and 2 dozen round with 3 small holes.
Bake on lightly greased sheet for 8 minutes.
Make a sandwich cookie by placing jam on bottom of 1 round, then place 1 round with hole on top.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sauerkraut and dried beef appetizers
directions: Mix all the ingredients well in a bowl.
Place about 1 teaspoon of mixture onto small rye breads and place in broiler just until tops of breads start to turn brown.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients like pie crust, until soft (with hands until aggression is relieved!!).
Flatten 1-inch balls of dough on ungreased cookie sheet with glass dipped in sugar (white).
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: butter herb baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter in preheated oven.
Meanwhile, in a 9-inch pie pan, combine cracker crumbs, cheese and spices.
Dip fish in butter and then crumb mixture.
Arrange fish in baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish is tender.
May use for chicken as well. Cook until tender.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Using a thick pan to cook in, mix syrup, salt and sugar.
Cook on high heat until forms a ball by dropping a little in a cup of cold water.
Add peanuts and stir constantly.
When peanuts start popping and turning tan, take off heat and stir in soda.
Pour into two buttered glass plates.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Simmer for 4 hours.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix ingredients and spread over ham while baking.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender in salted water.
Mix soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and mustard.
Add carrots, onion and pepper in glass dish.
Let marinate several hours or overnight.
Sauce can be used again when vegetables are gone for another batch.

title: marshmallow dressing for fruit
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and whip until fluffy.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Yield:
1 1/4 cups.

title: cheese cake
directions: Butter "spring type pan".
Press graham cracker crumbs on sides and bottom of pan.
In mixer, beat eggs, sugar, dash of salt, vanilla and cream cheese.
Beat until light and well blended.
Pour into crumb-lined pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
In another bowl, combine sour cream, vanilla, 1/2 cup sugar and dash of salt.
Mix ingredients together gently until well mixed.
Spread on top of cooked batter; bake an additional 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: roast beef salad
directions: Mix and set overnight.

title: creamy casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease a two quart round casserole.
Fry bacon in a ten inch skillet until crisp; remove from skillet and crumble.
Cook and stir onion, celery, green pepper, and mushrooms in bacon fat until tender.
Drain if necessary.
Stir in sour cream, cut up cooked meat, salt, pepper, and bacon.
Heat until bubbly and spread in casserole dish.
Mix Casserole Topping.
Spread over mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix artichokes and spices and place in a glass dish, then mix both sets of cheeses.
The dip should be baked at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove from the oven when all cheese is melted and serve hot with crackers (Wheat Thins preferred).

title: raisin molasses gems
directions: Beat shortening and 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt; add to molasses mixture.
Mix well. Stir in raisins.
Cover; refrigerate until chilled.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll each in sugar.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes, or until set.
Makes about 3 dozen Gems.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Prepare first 3 ingredients and toss lightly.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir lightly. Refrigerate.

title: chilled noodles with cucumbers and mushrooms
directions: Make salad dressing by combining the first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer for 5 minutes, cool, then chill.

title: date nut roll
directions: Cook milk, sugar and butter to soft ball stage; add vanilla. Add dates until melted.
Add nuts and roll in damp cloth.

title: texas cream gravy
directions: Heat bacon drippings with flour in sauce.
Stir constantly, cook but do not brown until smooth.
Add sausage that has been crumbled up and then pour in milk.
Mix and simmer until slightly thick.
Add salt and pepper.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Steam carrots; drain.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill 12 hours.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate one hour.

title: cajun rice and beans(with onions and cheese)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray medium size casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Layer in casserole the rice, beans, onion, celery and cheese.
Season each layer with small amount of seasonings and hot sauce.
Pour chicken broth over casserole. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed.
Entire recipe makes 8 servings.

title: canned apple pie filling(serves 7 quarts)
directions: Blend in large pan.
Stir in 10 cups water.
Cook over moderate heat.
Stir constantly until thick and bubbly.
Add 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Stir.
Divide in 7 quart jars.
Add sliced apples to fill jar.
Cold pack 15 to 20 minutes after water boils around cans.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Dip chicken pieces in mixture and place in casserole dish.
Pour rest of mixture over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until chicken is tender.

title: rose petal jelly
directions: Gather rose petals in early morning just after dew is gone. Yellow petals may be added if short of 2 quarts.
Red petals may be used, but they have a stronger flavor.
Pour the boiling water over the petals and steep until all color is gone.
Measure sugar into dish to add later.
Measure rose water and lemon juice into 6 or 8-quart kettle.
Add pectin and stir well.
Bring to boil; add sugar and mix well.
Continue stirring and bring to full boil. Boil exactly 2 minutes.
Skim and pour into prepared jars and seal.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together well in a bowl:
cream of chicken soup, Cheddar cheese, grated carrot, finely chopped onion, sour cream and salt and pepper.
Add zucchini.

title: crunchy crabmeat casserole
directions: Drain and slice water chestnuts.
Add soup, stuffing mix and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add crab and mix lightly.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion until lightly browned; drain.
Add salt, pepper, catsup, and tomato sauce; put in an 8-inch or 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Top with biscuits. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until biscuits are done underneath and golden brown.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat all together.
Add 1 cup nuts if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on a cookie sheet.

title: far east crab cakes
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well.
Shape crabmeat mixture into 8 patties.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add crabmeat patties and cook 6 to 8 minutes until lightly browned on both sides, turning once.
Transfer to a serving platter.
If desired, garnish with lemon wedges and green onion fan.
Serves 4 (about 125 calories per serving).

title: salmon strata
directions: Toast bread; trim crusts.
Mix butter and mustard.
Spread over 1 side of each bread slice.
Arrange 6 slices bread, buttered sides up, in ungreased baking dish (11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch). Heat oven to 350°.
Flake salmon, removing skin and bones.
Mix salmon, cheese, olives and onion.
Spread salmon mixture evenly over bread in baking dish.
Cut remaining 6 slices bread diagonally in half; place buttered sides up on salmon mixture. Rinse frozen peas under running cold water to separate; layer on bread.
Mix soup and milk; pour evenly on and around sandwiches. Bake, uncovered, until hot and bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with dill pickles.
Makes 6 to 9 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Grease a 6 x 8-inch baking pan.
Slice cooked sweet potatoes in half.
Place into baking pan, flat side down.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, brown sugar, milk, beaten egg yolks, salt and spices in top of double boiler.
Cook over boiling water, stirring often, about 10 minutes.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water; add marshmallows and let cool.
Add pineapple, bananas and 1/3 cup water to the Jell-O-marshmallow mixture.
Let set.
Cook pineapple juice, lemon juice, butter, egg, flour and sugar, stirring constantly, over low heat until thickened.
Let cool completely.
Beat whipped cream, adding cooled mixture; mix well.
Spread on Jell-O which has been set.
Spread cheese on top and serve.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix coloring and cocoa.
Let stand.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, then coloring-cocoa mix.
Beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla and vinegar; don't beat.
Bake at 350° in 2 (9-inch) or 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 35 minutes.

title: tomatoes parmesan
directions: Remove skins from tomatoes and quarter.
Place tomatoes in buttered casserole.
Melt butter.
Add garlic and basil.
Cube bread; add to seasoned butter.
Saute bread cubes over low heat for few minutes.
Spread bread cubes over tomatoes; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, then pull off of bone (or you can use about 5 chicken breasts).
Cook Stove Top as directed.
Fix soup, but not too thin.
Layer in casserole dish as follows: chicken, soup, stuffing, until finished.
Bake at 350° until top browns.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix according to directions for Gingersnap Pie Crust.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar together. Quarter biscuits and roll in sugar mixture (or put mixture in a large Ziploc bag and shake a few pieces at a time). Place in a greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle with pecans.

title: nuggets
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add eggs to milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk to the creamed mixture.
Add rolled oats, raisins, dates and nuts.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
May add water, a teaspoon at a time, to reach the preferred consistency.
May be served on a lettuce leaf with sliced tomatoes.
May be served with saltine crackers or with a favorite meat.

title: glazed meatballs(makes 5 dozen meatballs)
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, milk, egg and next 4 seasonings. Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in a large skillet and drain off fat.	Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet until jelly is melted, stirring constantly.
Add meatballs and stir until coated.	Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot in a chafing dish.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Cream butter; combine flour, cornstarch and sugar. Add to butter and mix well. Stir in walnuts. Roll into 3/4 inch balls. Place one inch apart on greased baking sheet. Bake 300°F for 20-25 minutes. Cool, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut flowers off broccoli stalks.
Rinse and let dry.
Chop onion.
In a large bowl, mix broccoli, onion, mayo and sugar.
Add shredded Mozzarella.
Mix well.
Chill upside down before serving.

title: kahlua trifle
directions: Bake cake according to directions; cool.
Break into small pieces and place in deep bowl.
Pour Kahlua over cake pieces.
Let soak overnight.
Make pudding according to directions.
Place a layer of cake in bottom of trifle bowl; follow with a layer of pudding and layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat this process about 3 times.
End with a good layer of Cool Whip (use more if you want). Top with grated Heath candy bar or Skor candy bar.
Enjoy!

title: aunt hazel's tater tot pie
directions: Brown 1 pound ground chuck and 1/2 large onion.
Drain. Spread in bottom of pan and top with Tater Tots.
Top that with 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Grate cheese over the top and bake at 350° until Tater Tots cook.

title: orange raisin sauce
directions: Mix flour, salt and brown sugar. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cook until thickened. Serve over ham slices.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic and pepper.
Spread in a 9 to 10-inch pie plate.
Layer remaining ingredients except the Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Top with cheese and bake
for 5 minutes more.
Serve as hot dip with chips, crackers or bread sticks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In large roasting pan, cook chicken until done.
While chicken is cooking, cook noodles on stove top.
After noodles and chicken are done, stir in chicken, noodles, cream of chicken, cream of mushroom soup and milk together.
Add in Philly cream cheese (break this up), salt and pepper.
Put sliced American cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Enjoy.

title: all american bean bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, lightly brown sliced frankfurters with onion, butter, mustard, allspice and pepper, mixing well.
Pour beans into a baking dish.
Add catsup and brown sugar; mix well.
Spread evenly over bottom of baking dish.
Layer frankfurters over the beans.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable quesadillas
directions: Saute onion and garlic in a little olive oil. When browned, add mushrooms. Cook and drain off any liquid from mushrooms cooking. Add green and red pepper, cook longer. Add chili and cilantro, spinach and carrot. Heat all ingredients through. Place tortilla on skillet add place vegetable mixture to one side. Top with cheese, fold over, and brown on both sides. Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, yogurt, onion, garlic salt and parsley.
Set aside.
Spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer 1/3 each of noodles, cottage cheese mixture, Mozzarella, sauce and Parmesan.
Repeat twice.
Pour water all around edges.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: puzzle cake
directions: Blend egg, salt and sugar together.
Sift flour with baking soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Add can of fruit cocktail with syrup. Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients and sprinkle on top of batter.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour. Cool; cut into squares.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut
eggplant
in cubes.
Boil for 10 minutes in salted water. Mix
remaining
ingredients except cheese.
Cook until thickened. In
casserole
dish,
coated
with
cooking spray, layer eggplant,
Mozzarella
cheese and tomato mixture twice. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Freezes well.

title: homemade silly putty
directions: You will need wax paper and Ziploc bag.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornflakes and cherries.
Beat well.
Form into 8 balls.
Roll each in cornflakes and top with 1/2 cherry.
Place on buttered baking sheet.
To serve:
Heat in preheated oven 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes.
(These freeze well.)

title: special sandwich
directions: Place cheese between bread.
Cook in margarine as would for grilled cheese, until bread is brown and cheese melted.
Open sandwich and put slices of bacon, slice of pineapple and close. You may use lettuce, mayonnaise and tomato, if you prefer.

title: deluxe asparagus casserole
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter; blend in flour.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Cool until thickened, stirring constantly.
In a medium casserole, arrange layer of half the asparagus, half the mushroom soup, 1 egg (sliced), 2 tablespoons butter, half of the cheese, half the white sauce and half the cracker crumbs.
Repeat layers, topping with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes, then cool.
Soften cream cheese.
Add 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix and spread over cooled crust.
Heat pineapple juice to boiling and dissolve jello in it.
Add strawberries and put in refrigerator until jelled.
Spread over second layer. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate cake brownies
directions: Sift sugar and flour together in large bowl.
Put oleo, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Bring to rapid boil and pour over sugar and flour, stir well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix and pour into greased and floured (16 x 11-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: simple cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese and butter thoroughly.
Work in the flour and cayenne pepper.
Chill 2 hours or longer.
Roll into balls 1 inch in diameter.
Bake in a very hot 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Yield: 30 puffs.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Stir in olive oil, Ranch dressing mix and vegetables.
Heat and serve.

title: root beer cake
directions: In bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
In large bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat.
Add dry ingredients alternately with 1 cup root beer. Mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs and margarine.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Pie must be completely cool before slicing.

title: hush puppies
directions: Stir together corn, meal, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar; place in bowl.
Add onions, butter, milk and water; mix well.
Add butter and egg; blend thoroughly.
Drop by small teaspoons into preheated fat.
Makes 30.

title: mama's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half batter into a well-greased pan.
Top with half the cheese, then repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: veggie tidbits
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet so there are no seams.
Cook according to directions on the package.
Mix mayo and dressing. Add to crust and top with your choice of chopped vegetables.
Cut into squares.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
You may hollow out a 1 loaf rye bread.
Cube the bread and serve the dip in the hollowed crust.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix a little at a time. Grease muffin pans and drop into each with a spoon. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook chopped onion in oleo until transparent.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in a covered dish for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.

title: "philly" fudge *
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft and smooth.
Slowly blend in sugar.
Add melted chocolate.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, salt and pecans; mix well.
Press into greased shallow pan.
Refrigerate until firm and cut into squares.
For a slightly softer fudge, blend in
1 teaspoon of cream.

title: hot tail gate punch
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer 1 to 2 hours. Serve in crock-pot or in a cleaned out pumpkin. Pumpkin keeps punch warm but does not change the flavor of punch. Serves 4.

title: chicken on a cloud
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onions.
Place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Add several pats of butter.
Add chicken breasts on top.
Pour can of cream of chicken soup diluted with milk over the dish.
Add pats of butter.
Add paprika for color.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: turkey puff
directions: Combine turkey, celery, onion, salad dressing and salt.
Trim crusts of 4 bread slices; set bread aside.
Dice crusts and remaining slices; place in a baking dish.
Top with turkey mixture.
Triangle 4 slices to decorate top.
Combine milk and eggs; pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, until brown. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: brown and white cookies
directions: Mix and shape cookies with a spoon.
Bake at 350°F for 15 - 20 min.

title: buckeye candy balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into small balls and refrigerate until very cold.
Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Add a little vegetable oil.
Drop several balls at a time to coat them.
Use tongs to remove them and place on waxed paper lined cookie sheet. Refrigerate until coating is firm.

title: grandma's biscuits
directions: Grandma places her flour in a large bowl, make a well in the center of it, and add the shortening and milk to it.
Work it together and roll it out.
Cut out small biscuits or pinch off a small amount.
Roll in hand, put in greased pan.
Bake in a 425° oven until golden brown.
Take out and butter the tops.
Makes about 3 dozen biscuits.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in frying pan.
Drain grease.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and seasonings.
Fry for 20 minutes.
Transfer to large pot.
Add tomato sauce and juice.
Cook one hour.
Add kidney beans and boil for 5 minutes more.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple; add gelatin.
Let cool; add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into molds or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 12 servings.

title: frozen pickled cucumbers
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers and mix onion, pepper, vinegar, sugar, celery and mustard seed and salt.
Mix well.
Let set for 2 or 3 hours.
Mix it good about every 30 minutes.
Put in boxes and freeze.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Saute onion, bell pepper and mushrooms in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and place in 2 pie shells which have been baked according to package instructions.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and continue baking for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown. Serves 10 people.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Rub the potato skins with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.
Allow to cool to touch.
Cut large potatoes in half or cut small portion off tops of smaller potatoes.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell.
Mash potato pulp with butter, chives, salt, pepper and milk.
Add milk as needed. Carefully stuff potato shells.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: "peanut blossoms" cookies
directions: Blend peanut butter and shortening in large mixer bowl until fluffy.
Add in egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour. Continue beating.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar. Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet in preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Immediately place kiss on each cookie, pressing down so that cookie "cracks" around edges. Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack.

title: rachel pafford's korean beef
directions: Slice beef into 1/8-inch slices, then cut into 2-inch wide strips.
Chop bell pepper.
Chop onions, including tops.
Put beef into large bowl with lid.
Pour in soy sauce, chopped pepper, onions, sugar and mushrooms.
Mix well; cover and let marinate in refrigerator for at least 8 hours.
Turn oven on broil; pour beef mixture into broiler pan with onions, bell pepper, mushrooms and sauce.
Place meat in a single layer.
(If pan is not large enough, 2 pans may be used, but make sure you halve the marinating ingredients, also.)
Place in oven and cook about 8 minutes or until done.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 10.
Goes good with fried rice or stir-fried vegetables.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine and mix well.
Let set overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut
biscuits
in 4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and roll each
biscuit
piece in the mixture.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Drop biscuits in pan.
Pour remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture
over biscuits.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Melt margarine and brown sugar and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: triscuits dip
directions: Rinse beef in warm water.
Mix all ingredients together. Chill.
Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in lard.
Mix eggs, vinegar and water.
Add all to flour.
Makes 20 to 21 crusts.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in glass dish.

title: raspberry cordial
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium high heat, bring sugar with water to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Turn off heat and cool to room temperature.
Stir in vodka.
Place raspberries in a tall 2-quart (8-cup) glass jar with lid.
Pour in vodka syrup.
Cover and store in a cool dark place for 1 month, shaking the jar lightly once a week.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix everything together; put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind vegetables together
and sprinkle with salt.
Let set overnight.
In morning,
rinse
and
drain
well with cold water. Mix
together
the
following
ingredients:
sugar, vinegar, cornstarch, turmeric, nutmeg, celery seed and pepper. Bring to boil in
large
kettle.
Add vegetables and simmer 30 minutes. Ladle into hot jars.
Water bath for 15 minutes.

title: crabmeat hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix crabmeat, cheese and margarine; spread mixture on muffin halves.
Cut in 6ths and freeze.
To serve, bake until bubbly. Good!

title: jiffy tacos
directions: Crumble ground beef into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Microwave at High for 6 to 7 minutes, stirring at 2-minute intervals.
When meat is done, drain away grease.
Spoon 3 tablespoons meat mixture into each taco shell; top with lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with taco sauce.

title: orange torte cake
directions: Mix according to directions on the box.
(I usually divide batter into 3 round cake pans.)
Then bake according to directions.

title: saucy louisiana chicken
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Add green pepper and chicken.
Cook 5 minutes or until pepper is tender-crisp and chicken is cooked.
Blend tomatoes, cornstarch and cayenne.
Add to skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and translucent.
Add green beans and heat through.
Serve with rice, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oriental rice
directions: Melt butter.
Saute celery and onion.
Pour over rice.
Mix all other ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diet cole slaw
directions: Combine and bring to a boil vinegar, dry mustard, onion powder, lemon juice, celery seed and salt.
Sprinkle Sugar Twin over cabbage.
Pour boiling mixture over cabbage.
Cover immediately and let stand 4 to 6 hours.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Pinch cake and place pieces in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pudding and ice cream; pour over cake.
Next, mix Jell-O and strawberries; pour over cake, then refrigerate.

title: mini cheese cakes(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press equal portions onto bottoms of lightly greased or paper-lined muffin cups.
In mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon equal amounts of mixture (about 3 tablespoons) into prepared cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool.
Chill.
Garnish as desired.

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften cheese and cream with sugar.
Mix Jell-O and hot water. Add to cheese/sugar mixture. Whip chilled condensed milk. Add vanilla. Fold into cheese/Jell-O mixture. Chill.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef, onion, garlic salt, salt, pepper and oregano. Pour off any grease.
Add Ragu and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Beat eggs and mix with cottage cheese.

title: dairy potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix together potatoes, soup, sour cream, onion, cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350°.
Halfway through cooking time, top with buttered corn flake crumbs.
If using frozen hash browns, cook 40 to 45 minutes.
If using cooked, cubed potatoes, cook for 25 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain.
Mix cornbread, peppers and corn.
Pour half of mixture into greased baking dish.
Add hamburger meat on top.
Top with cheese. Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° until done. Top
will begin to brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cream shortening sugar and vanilla.
Then add one egg at a time, beating thoroughly.
Stir in pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients alternating with water until smooth.
Add chopped nuts and pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: summer punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: gold butter cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Bake in sheet pan or three 9-inch cake pans at 375° until done.

title: brunch special
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Saute meat and green pepper.
Spread half of bread cubes in a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle half of meat mixture and put cheese over. Repeat.
Pour eggs and milk mixture over.
Let stand 1/2 hour or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: the a b c cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to moderate (350°).
Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter in medium-size bowl until well blended.
Press mixture against bottom and side of lightly buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese in a medium-size bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in the 1 cup sugar and egg yolks.
Stir in 1 teaspoon of the vanilla.
Beat egg whites in a small bowl until stiff.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake cake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 40 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven. Increase oven temperature to very hot (475°).

title: fantastic fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and orange segments.
Put apple pieces in juice (to keep from discoloring).
Drain apples; mix all fruit and pie filling with sweetener or sugar.
Chill well.
Serve topped with Cool Whip.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Mix corn flakes and butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cherry-o-cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and whip until light.
Add Eagle Brand milk and mix until blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well and place in graham cracker pie shell.
Chill several hours.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and cornstarch.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° until thick and brown on top.

title: squash or pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine the squash, sugar, oil and eggs in a large bowl and heat together.
Add dry ingredients and stir.
Stir in chocolate chips, if desired.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: walnut crescents
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Mix in water and vanilla, then flour and nuts.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Roll out in long rolls 1/2 inch across.
Cut in 3 inch lengths and shape in crescents.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes in 325° oven.
Do not brown.
Take out and roll in confectioners sugar while warm.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and blend with the sugar.
Add melted margarine, milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pastry and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: moon beans(sugar-free)
directions: Mix all together.
Roll in balls, then roll in coconut.

title: grandma's apple grunt
directions: Using a mid-sized glass dish, grease dish with oleo. Slice apples into dish until dish is 2/3 full. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon and pour over the apples. In another dish, mix shortening the size of an egg, egg, sugar, flour, baking powder, and salt and and mix. Pour enough milk in to make a thick dough. Pour over apples. Bake at 350° until brown and done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine pasta, celery, onion, seafood and olives.
Mix and coat well with salad dressing.
Add spices to taste.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: terrific dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all the ingredients and chill.
Wonderful for dipping any fresh vegetables!

title: texas hash
directions: Brown hamburger with green pepper, onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce.
Put stewed tomatoes in blender, then add to hamburger.
Add chili powder to taste.
Boil noodles until done. Layer noodles, sauce and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake covered for 30 minutes, then uncovered for 15 minutes.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes total.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Squeeze out all the liquid.
Chop finely water chestnuts.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar and butter (barely melted).
Mix soda with buttermilk and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and work in flour. Roll dough lightly.
Add extra flour until rolled out like biscuits and cut.
Bake at 375°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: veggie mix
directions: Cut into bite size pieces.

title: beef-minestrone soup
directions: In a large pot, cover beef with 7 cups water.
Add seasonings, vinegar, tomato paste, quartered tomatoes and onion.
Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 hours.
Remove meat.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Discard any fat and bone.
Return to pot.
Add vegetables and simmer 45 minutes longer.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.
Next night, bring to boil.
Add macaroni and kidney beans.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix well flour, butter and chopped walnuts.
Spread in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan and pat firmly.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.

title: roasted eggplant and garlic soup
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a mixing bowl, combine the garlic, herbs and drizzle of olive oil together.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Split the eggplant in half, lengthwise, and smear the garlic mixture over the top of each eggplant half. Place the eggplant on a baking sheet and place in the oven.
Roast the eggplant for 30 minutes or until the eggplant is tender. Remove from the oven and cool.
Using a spoon, remove the flesh of the eggplant and discard the skin.
Heat the oil in a 2-quart saucepan.
When the oil is hot, add the onions.
Saute for 2 minutes.
Add the roasted eggplant and garlic; continue to saute for 2 minutes.
Stir in the stock and bring the liquid to a boil. Reduce to a simmer and cook for 10 minutes.
Using a handheld blender, puree the soup until smooth.
Stir in the cream and continue to simmer for 3 minutes.
Season the soup with the salt and the cayenne.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place layers in Pyrex or Corning Ware dish until your dish is almost full.
Just keep layering it.
Add salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup milk.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Add sliced cheese.
Cover top while still hot with cheese.
Cook covered.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Cut sherbet up in pineapple juice; add ginger ale.
This makes 1 punch bowl full.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Close seams.
Brown sausage and drain.
Sprinkle sausage on dough.
Mix cheese and put on top of sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and oregano. Pour on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cream together until smooth in large bowl and then add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Serve on lettuce. Serves about 6 to 8.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Make a smooth paste of water, flour and a pinch of salt. Boil 1 cup berries with sugar and 1/2 cup water. Add flour paste and stir until it thickens. Remove from heat. Cool. When cool, add the remaining berries and put in pie shell. Refrigerate. Top with Cool Whip when it is cool.

title: london broil
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Cook and stir onions and 1/4 teaspoon salt in butter until onions are tender.
Keep warm over low heat.
Stir together salad oil, lemon juice, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the pepper; brush on top side of meat.
Set oven control at broil and/or 550°.
Broil meat about 5 minutes or until brown.
Turn meat; brush with oil mixture and broil just until rare, 5 minutes longer.
Cut meat across grain at a slanted angle into very thin slices.
Serve with onions.

title: mississippi goulash
directions: Cook hamburger until its brown; drain.
In same skillet, add onion, green pepper, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cayenne pepper.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add cooked rice.
Stir together.
Let simmer another 5 minutes.
Turn off.
Put shredded cheese on top to melt, then serve.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put sliced cucumbers in large glass container.
Soak overnight in 1/4 bag lime.
Be sure to cover in water; cover container.

title: onion cheese pie
directions: Mix crushed crackers with melted butter or margarine.
Press into Pyrex pie plate, reserving 1/2 cup.
Saute onions in vegetable oil until tender and golden; spread on crust.
Heat milk, eggs, salt, cheese and seasonings, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Pour mixture over onions and bake until center sets, about 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well.
Add egg, buttermilk and oil; mix well.
Add raisins; mix well again.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven in round greased and floured pan.

title: leftover roast
directions: Cut roast into bite size pieces and put in pan.
Use 1 or 2 cans of mushroom soup (1/3 cup of milk per can of soup) per amount of roast you have left.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Prepare rice. Pour meat mixture over rice.

title: fat-free philly spread
directions: Mix well.
Makes 1 1/2 cups (0 fat, 244 calories) or 24 tablespoons equals 72 teaspoons.
(One teaspoon equals 0 fat and 3 1/2 calories.)
This is good with SnackWell's crackers.
Cracker plus spread equals 0 fat and 9 1/2 calories.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Add peas and tuna fish.
Mix thoroughly.

title: noodle pudding(kugel)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add noodles.
Pour into well-buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours until top peaks are browned.

title: hash brown cheese casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, cheese, 1 stick margarine, sour cream, cream of chicken soup and onion flakes.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix 1/4 cup margarine with corn flake crumbs.
Spread on potato mixture.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma rettig's homemade bread
directions: Microwave 2 cups milk for 5 to 6 minutes until hot and skim forms on top.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rolls using bread machine
directions: Put
all
ingredients
in
bread machine and let knead. Then let rise, put in pans according to rolls or bread and let rise again
and
bake
at
375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini casserole #1
directions: Cook zucchini and onion until tender.
Drain.
Add drained carrots, Miracle Whip, chicken soup and Stove Top stuffing.
Stir together.
Melt butter and pour over.
Stir together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple raisin sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in small saucepan.
Stir in apple juice, lemon juice and raisins.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and boil 1 minute.
Add butter or margarine.
Stir until melted.
Serve hot with ham or pork.

title: chow noodle candy
directions: Put chocolate and butterscotch morsels in double boiler to melt.
Add	noodles.
Lightly
stir.
Add
nuts and drop on greased cookie sheet.

title: apricot-glazed pork roast
directions: Season roast with salt and pepper.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: prairie apple crunch
directions: Place apples in a greased 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with mix of sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Pour over cream and vanilla.

title: pineapple squash bake
directions: Wash squash and cut in half.
Remove seeds and membrane and sprinkle lightly with salt.
Turn upside-down in a flat baking pan and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pineapple.
Turn squash cups right side up and fill with pineapple mixture.
Drizzle butter over the tops; return to the oven and continue to bake until the squash is tender, about 25 minutes longer.

title: tang salad
directions: Mix instant
pudding mix with Tang, then with pineapple juice. Mix
pineapple
tidbits,
mandarin
oranges
and fruit cocktail with Tang mixture. Chill.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add corn, margarine, salt and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in a 400° oven.
Bake about 30 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple, dry pudding mix and Cool Whip until blended. Stir in nuts. Chill until serving time.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Put sherbet in punch bowl.
Add 7-Up, a liter at a time, until sherbet is mixed enough to drink.
Don't mix too much 7-Up.
It will be too thin.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, egg and garlic salt and pepper.
Roll into balls about a inch or inch and a half.
In a large baking bowl, mix grape jelly and chili sauce and a dash of lemon juice. Put in microwave.
Melt together.
Place meatballs in sauce and bake for about 40 minutes to an hour on 350°.
Stir about halfway through baking time.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Blend oil, sugar and eggs. Mix well. Add rest of ingredients. Put in greased and floured 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date-nut cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients. Mix both mixtures together and bake at 325° about 30 minutes. Leave in oblong pan.

title: meat and veggie skillet
directions: Fry cabbage, onions and potatoes until almost tender. Add kielbasa. Cook until potatoes are tender and meat is heated through. Quick and good!

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° to 375° until golden brown.

title: metial starter
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in a warm place for 3 to 4 days.
Put in refrigerator and leave for 3 days.
Remove and feed with 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons potato flakes and 1 cup warm water.
Save 1 cup of starter and throw away the rest.
Do not make bread now.
Return remaining starter to refrigerator and repeat the feeding process 2 more times after 3 times feeding. Make bread with 1 cup of starter.
Return initial starter to the refrigerator and follow sourdough process every 3 to 5 days.

title: pea salad
directions: Place frozen peas in strainer; pour boiling water over peas. In a bowl, mix all ingredients.
Cubed Cheddar cheese can be used. Refrigerate at least 1/2 hour.

title: fudge cookies
directions: In saucepan, add sugar, butter, salt, milk and cocoa.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
While mixture is still hot, add peanut butter.
Mix in nuts or coconut, oats and vanilla.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper; cool.

title: topaz apple dessert
directions: Separate biscuits and arrange on bottom of greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Place apples over biscuits.
Combine remaining ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over apples and biscuits and bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream topping.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken with bay leaves until cooked; cut into cubes. Mix with remaining ingredients. Place in 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Cover with 2 cans (2.8 ounces each) French-fried onions. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese (8-ounces or 2 cups). Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: a fast made meal
directions: Add small amount of milk into soup.
Mix all together and cook in oven 10 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas crisps
directions: Drain juice from pickles; slice or cut into chunks.
Rinse original jar and dry.
Layer sugar, pickles, garlic and Tabasco in jar.
Cap and let jar sit until sugar dissolves, about 15 minutes. Turn a couple of times to help sugar liquefy.
Refrigerate for 3 days before serving.
Makes 1 quart of Christmas green-colored pickles.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in one layer in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Mix together soups and wine; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese over top and bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mock mosa
directions: Combine ingredients, mix well and pour into glass with crushed ice.

title: pecan pull-apart
directions: Separate dough from each can into 4 rectangles.
Cut each rectangle in half lengthwise.
Roll dough strips into ropes.
Dip each rope into margarine, then roll in combined sugar, cinnamon and nut mixture.
Line a 14-inch pizza pan with aluminum foil; grease well.
Starting at center of pan, loosely arrange ropes in a spiral fashion.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Sprinkle leftover sugar, cinnamon and nut mixture on top before cooking.
Serve warm.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Drain.
Combine rice, celery and soup mix with sausage mixture.
Place in a greased 3-quart casserole.
Add 5 cups boiling water.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Top with almonds last 15 minutes.
Can be put together ahead and cooked 30 minutes.
Finish cooking at serving time.

title: crumb cake deluxe
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, butter and salt until crumbly.
Set aside 1 cup.
Stir baking soda, cinnamon and cloves into the remaining crumb mixture.
Add egg and buttermilk; mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes or until the cake tests done.

title: mock cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine and cook about 15 minutes or until tender the first 5 ingredients.
When tender, place all in a blender and add remaining ingredients.
Blend about 1 minute at high speed; pour into saucepan and heat prior to serving.
Yields about 6 cups.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In small saucepan, heat chocolate chips, milk and honey over medium heat, stirring constantly until blended.
Serve warm. Makes 1 cup.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks; add condensed milk and lime juice.
Beat until thick.
Beat 1 egg white until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Put pie in oven 8 minutes to firm.
Beat 3 egg whites.
Blend in sugar and cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff and forms peaks.
Bake until egg whites are golden brown.

title: fried rice
directions: In nonstick skillet or wok, saute onions, green pepper and celery until tender-crisp.
Add rice and stir-fry until heated through.
Add meat, eggs and soy sauce; stir-fry until egg sets. Serve hot.

title: parisian balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Using about 1 teaspoon of batter, roll into a ball and place on cookie sheet.
Freeze all the balls.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Boil chicken; debone and cut up into small chunks. Boil noodles until tender. Mix soup with leftover chicken broth. Stir in chicken pieces and noodles. Add salt to taste. Cook for 5 minutes.

title: cocoa kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Line 2 large cookie sheets with foil. In small bowl beat at high speed egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
At low speed, beat in cocoa and almond extract until blended.
Fold in almonds, reserving 1 tablespoon.
Drop mixture by slightly rounded tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheets, sprinkle tops with reserved almonds.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until set.
Cool on cookie sheets 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: banana split salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving 1/2 cup of juice; set this aside.
In a pan, bring water to a boil; remove from heat.
Add gelatin and marshmallows; stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially set. Toss bananas with lemon juice; fold bananas and pineapple into gelatin.
Pour into an 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm. Combine sugar, flour and salt in pan.
Stir in egg and reserved pineapple juice.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in butter.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream; spread over gelatin.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Chill overnight. Serves 9.

title: fruit fluff
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Melt butter or margarine in 8 x 8-inch baking pan in 350° oven.
When melted, pour into first ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pan and bake 5 minutes, then add fruit and bake an additional 30 minutes or until done.

title: maple bars
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool.
Add yeast, softened in warm water.
Add egg and flour.
Let rise for 2 hours. Roll out and cut in bars with knife.
Let rise until very large and fry in fat (melted Crisco).
Frost with powdered sugar and maple flavoring.

title: frozen tortoni with strawberry sauce
directions: Soften ice cream slightly.
Stir in macaroons and 4 tablespoons of juice.
Whip the cream until thick and shiny; fold into ice cream mixture.
Spoon into 3-cup metal dish or mold. Sprinkle surface slightly with powdered sugar and almonds.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Freeze until firm, about 4 or 5 hours or overnight.
To unmold, wrap mold for 4 or 5 seconds in a towel wrung out with hot water.
Loosen edge with spatula; turn onto cold platter.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix together with wooden or plastic spoon, sugar, flour, milk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir until mixture is smooth.

Lumps will appear but continue to mix until only a few lumps appear. Melt butter or margarine and pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Pour apple pie filling into pan; spread evenly across bottom of pan.
Pour mixture in bowl over top of apple pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (cooking time may vary).

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt cheese. Mix with soups and milk. Add chicken and noodle. Bake at 350 until bubbly.

title: potato wedges
directions: Combine water and next 5 ingredients in baking dish.
Add potatoes, tossing to coat.
Cover and microwave on High 8 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: cheese logs
directions: Let set to room temperature.
Mix with hands.
Roll into logs on wax paper sprinkled with 1 tablespoon cayenne pepper and 1 tablespoon paprika. Makes 3 logs.

title: buttermilk lemon pie
directions: In large saucepan combine 1 1/3 cup of sugar and 1/2 cup of flour.
Gradually stir in 2 cups buttermilk and 1/2 cup of water.

title: busy day chocolate cake
directions: Bring oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water to a rapid boil.
Pour over flour and sugar; beat well.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Bake in flat pan for 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: old fashioned stew(basic stew mixture)
directions: Melt shortening in Dutch oven. Brown a portion of the meat on all sides in hot shortening. Remove browned meat from Dutch oven. Set aside. Repeat until all meat is brown. Return to Dutch oven. Add water, onions, garlic and salt. Simmer, covered, until meat is tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours. When cold, skim fat. Pour stew mixture into 3 (1-quart) freezer containers. Seal, label and freeze. Makes 3 quarts.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash bean mixture.
Add salt and enough water to cover over 1 inch.
Soak overnight.
Drain and add 2 quarts of water along with ham chunks, diced onion and garlic.
Simmer until tender.
Add 1 can of tomatoes and 1 whole hot pepper (optional).
Simmer 1 more hour.
Can also be done in crock-pot.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add rice and potatoes.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Add remaining vegetables (except grated carrots) and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
In a heavy pot over medium-high heat, melt margarine.
Add 2 tablespoons water and carrots.
Saute 4 to 5 minutes.
Add to soup.
Put 1 teaspoon sour cream in soup when served.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble 1/2 of corn bread in salad bowl.
Mix together salad dressing mix with sour cream and miracle whip.
Combine tomatoes, red bell peppers, green bell peppers, and green onions and toss on top of cornbread.
Top with 1/2 of beans, tomato mixture, cheese, bacon, corn, and dressing.
Repeat the layers and top off with the rest of the dressing.
Cover and chill 3 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix water with soup in baking dish.
Add all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9x13 greased pan.
Put Eagle Brand Milk and cream of coconut in holes that have been punched in cake.
Put cool whip and frozen coconut on top.

title: easy oven beef and vegetable stew
directions: Remove all visible fat from beef; cut beef into 1 inch cubes. In large casserole, toss beef with flour.
Add onions, potatoes, carrots, garlic, turnip, water, beef stock, tomato sauce, thyme, oregano, pepper, bay leaf, and orange rind.
Stir to mix.
Bake uncovered in 325 degree oven for 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaf.
Serve.

title: dill dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sour cream and salad dressing. Fold in dill, chives, parsley and Worcestershire sauce; mix well and refrigerate. Serve with carrot sticks, celery sticks, cherry tomatoes, broccoli florets, bell pepper sticks or cauliflower florets, etc.

title: june's bok choy salad
directions: Mix sunflower seeds, crumbled noodles and melted margarine together.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Watch carefully as it will burn easily.
Store in plastic bag in refrigerator when cool.

title: hot brie pasta a'la diane
directions: Cut cheese into chunks.
Combine with next 6 ingredients in a large bowl and let stand for 2 hours at room temperature.
Cook pasta, drain and toss with Brie mixture.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Strain.
Add onion. Pour over hot cabbage.
Serves 8.

title: italian rocks
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes a stiff mixture.
Roll in little balls about the size of walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Be sure only to brown slightly.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until soft.
Drain macaroni and run cold water over macaroni.
Mix macaroni with Miracle Whip.
Add relish, chopped tuna, eggs and onions.
Mix.
Season to taste with Lawry's seasoning and paprika.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados with a fork.
Blend in lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients and combine thoroughly.
Serve with corn chips.

title: cranberry-cream cheese frosties
directions: Crush cranberry sauce with fork.
Add lemon juice. Pour into paper cups or 1-quart refrigerator tray or 1-quart flat dish. Whip cream cheese.
Add the mayo, powdered sugar, walnuts and whipped cream.
Pour over the cranberry sauce and freeze. If in paper cups, split and peel off paper.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: simple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and juice with pudding.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Top with cherries.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt the butter or oleo; add flour and blend.
Add beet liquid; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and cloves; stir until sugar dissolves. Drain beets.
Add.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chinese new year cookies
directions: Melt bits together.
Mix in noodles and nuts. Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper. Chill.
Makes 96 cookies.

title: breakfast treat
directions: Lightly butter bread.
Put 6 slices in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with a layer of sausage and a layer of cheese.
Repeat with other 6 slices of bread and sausage.

title: tomato and celery soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy large pot over medium heat.
Add tomatoes and bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until tomatoes are soft and juicy, about 20 minutes.
Strain tomatoes through sieve over heavy large saucepan, pressing with back of spoon.
Add diced celery to tomatoes and bring to boil. Reduce heat to low and cook 5 minutes.
Season with sugar, salt and pepper.
(Can be prepared one day ahead, cool, cover and refrigerate, re-warm before continuing.)
Ladle soup into bowls. Spoon dollop of cream over serving.
Sprinkle with croutons and garnish with celery leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Combine flour, margarine and nuts.
Spread in an oblong pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Let stand, then spread on cream cheese mixture.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion and butter until transparent.
Stir in flour and cook for 5 minutes.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Stir in grated cheese and blend until smooth.
Puree 1/2 of broccoli pieces in blender and leave rest of broccoli in pieces.
Slowly blend chicken broth into sauce.
Add puree and pieces of broccoli.
Stir well.
Simmer 15 minutes and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: trailside oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat margarine, peanut butter and sugars until creamy.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, then oats and raisins.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful, leaving space for expansion.
Drop on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool.
Makes 42 cookies. Per cookie:
134 calories, 5 g. fat and 12 mg. cholesterol.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix apples and chopped candy bars until well blended. Gently stir in whipped topping. Refrigerate one hour or until ready to serve. Garnish with apple slices. Salad is best made and served the same day. Makes 20 servings.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and bell peppers.
Cook until tender.
Add enough water to cover the mixture.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and red pepper.
Let boil 5 minutes.
Add cooked rice. (Mixture should not have very much water left.)
Stuff whole peppers.
(Boil bell peppers to be stuffed for a few minutes or until tender.)
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pancho's dip
directions: Liquify all except cheese in blender.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cheese, grated.
Put half of cheese in one half of liquid into blender and liquify.
Pour into bowl and do other half.
May be served with chips.

title: inez's pink salad
directions: Mix together condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Add crushed pineapple, nuts, coconut, marshmallows and pie filling.
Mix well. Pour into dish.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: coconut shortbread
directions: Mix in order given.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight. Slice and place on ungreased sheets.
Bake in 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 or 9-inch pie.

title: oriental hash
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet, stirring until crumbly. Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Simmer, covered, for 3 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soups
together
until smooth and pour in bottom of large casserole
dish.
Put
chicken, which has been separated from bones, on top of soup.
Drain Veg-All and place on top of chicken. Mix
together
margarine, flour and milk.	Pour over top of all layers.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown beef, celery and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add a can of green beans or any vegetable.
Put in baking dish, pour soup over mix and put Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon sauce bread
directions: First, mix cinnamon with applesauce.
Next, put the bread in a microwave-safe dish and spread the applesauce on the front of the bread.
Put bread in microwave 15 seconds.
Make sure bread is a bit moist and peel off the crust.
Last, eat it!

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain the vegetables and place in large mixing bowl.
Add chopped onion and chopped celery; stir to mix well.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and Provolone cheese.
Combine with vegetables.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with the crushed crackers.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons melted butter over crackers and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes or until it begins to bubble.
Serve immediately.

title: strawberry shortcake(in punch bowl)
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, blend well after each.
Add milk and flavoring, mix well.
Add flour slowly, mix well.
Use 3 (9-inch) pans, greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Chop unpeeled zucchini, shallots and garlic.
Put all 3 into a heavy frying pan.
Cook for 10 to 20 minutes (stir to keep from burning, you don't want it to be brown).
Put all ingredients into blender and blend.
Add table cream.
Heat and serve hot with croutons, or chill and serve cold with chives.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh raspberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, milk, flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; place unwashed berries, hole side up, in batter.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with white icing while still slightly warm.

title: fast pizza dough
directions: In a large bowl, mix two cups flour, salt, sugar and yeast. Quickly stir in hot water.
In same bowl, work in remaining cup of flour.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Shape or roll to fit pan.
Top with favorite pizza goodies.

title: oven-baked potatoes
directions: Dip potatoes in olive oil and place on cookie sheet. Add salt and Mrs. Dash Table Blend seasoning to taste. Bake at 350° until fork-tender.

title: pound cake
directions: Measure all ingredients into bowl and then beat for 5 minutes.
Spoon batter into greased and floured bunt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: oklahoma cherry dessert
directions: Crust:
Melt butter.
Mix 1/4 cup powdered sugar, flour and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°, or until brown.

title: chicken stir fry
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic powder and prick chicken with fork. Marinate in Dales sauce for 15 minutes. Put in a large fry pan or a stir fry pan and simmer with lid on med/low until tender. Flip chicken occasionally. Remove from pan and chop or slice chicken. Put back in pan and add vegetables. Sprinkle with garlic powder or chopped garlic and simmer until vegetables are slightly tender. You may need to add a little more sauce.

title: radishes in cream
directions: Make a dressing of all ingredients, except the radishes. Combine the radishes and dressing and mix well.
Serve on a lettuce leaf cup.
Serves 4.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a floured 8-inch loaf pan or two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Measure all ingredients, scraping sides and bottom of bowl.
Constantly pour into pans.
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pan; cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar (1 cup).
Add eggs and mix well. Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk in few additions.
Stir in lemon rind.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Have the lemon juice and 1/4 cup sugar ready.
Mix well and pour over loaf when taken from the oven.
Let bread cool in pan before serving.
Makes several servings.

title: jewish-american cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan. Beat cream cheese with
cottage
cheese
at
high speed, until they are well combined.
Gradually
beat
in sugar, then eggs. At low speed beat
in cornstarch, flour, lemon juice, rind and vanilla.
Add the melted
butter
and
sour
cream.
Beat just until it is smooth.
Pour
into
greased pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until firm around edges.
Turn off oven; let pan sit in oven for 2 hours,
out
of oven another 2 hours.
Chill in refrigerator 3 hours
or
until well chilled.
Pour desired topping
over cheesecake.
This
cheesecake
is
sold
in
New York's finest restaurants.

title: cinnamon fruit dip
directions: Prepare yogurt by straining to sour cream consistency (takes approximately 2 hours).
Place yogurt in strainer lined with a coffee filter, plain paper towel or cheesecloth.
Place bowl underneath to catch when draining out.
Refrigerate while straining.
Blend strained yogurt, marshmallow cream and cinnamon well using blender or electric mixer.
Refrigerate until served. Serve with assorted fresh fruit.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups or 40 (1 tablespoon) servings.
Contains 20 calories per tablespoon and only a trace of fat.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Sift all dry ingredients together. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture of oil and sugar. Stir vanilla and carrots into this. Bake in three 10-inch greased and floured pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add onion and cook slowly until soft.
Add ground beef and garlic.
Stir until lightly browned. Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat, taste and add more salt, if needed.
Serve over rice, noodles, etc.
Serves 4.

title: janeen lee's butternut squash pie
directions: Beat eggs and stir into squash.
Mix in remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook the onion and green pepper in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute.
Stir in corn and eggs.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Sprinkle evenly over corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: puritan punch
directions: Pour juice over sherbet, garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.
Add ginger ale and serve.

title: tomato mac 'n meat
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Brown onion and meat; drain grease.
Stir in soup, water and pepper.
Fold drained macaroni into tomato mixture.
If cheese topping is desired, put Tomato Mac 'N Meat in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 325° until cheese melts.

title: tater dish
directions: Mix and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: caramelized brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: favorite beef loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Shape mixture in a loaf pan.
Press 2 green pepper rings and onion ring atop meat loaf. Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange banana shake
directions: Blend all ingredients except fruit slices until smooth and pour into chilled glasses.
Decorate with orange and lime slices.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease	two
15 1/2 x 2-inch baking sheets.
Keep warm. Place sugar,
corn
syrup
and
water
in a 3 quart casserole. Cook in microwave
on Full power for 8 to 10 minutes or until soft	ball stage
is
reached.
Stir
occasionally.
Stir
in peanuts.
Cook in microwave for 10 to 12 minutes or until hard crack
stage
is reached.
At
this	stage, when dropped into water	the
syrup separates
into
threads which are hard and brittle.
Stir	in butter and baking soda.
Pour half of candy on
each sheet, spreading to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cook.
Break into pieces.

title: brazil nut cookies
directions: Add sugar and salt to ground nuts and mix well.
Beat egg white until it holds a soft peak.
Add to nut mixture and combine thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart.
Flatten by pressing with bottom of glass covered with a damp cloth.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: shrimp patties
directions: Baking powder may be used to make them higher.

title: open-face pear pie
directions: Use fully ripe Bartlett pears.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: On low heat saute onion, garlic and bell pepper in oil until onion is transparent.
Add crawfish, tomato sauce and season to taste.
Add parsley and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch dissolved in water as desired.

title: upside-down apple cake
directions: Grease one 9-inch round glass pie plate.
Spread brown sugar over bottom of plate and press down evenly.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter and drizzle over sugar.
Arrange apple slices overlapping around edge of pan.
Fill center with remaining slices.
Compact gently with hands.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and remaining teaspoon cinnamon.
Cream the remaining 1/2 cup butter and granulated sugar until light.
Add egg and beat until fluffy.
Add buttermilk and flour mixture alternately until smooth.
Carefully spread over apple mixture, making sure edges are sealed.
Bake on center rack of oven at 350° for approximately 60 minutes.
Loosen edges while still warm (not hot) and invert onto serving plate. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Can be reheated in microwave.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Mix with cole slaw, onions, sunflower seeds, almonds or pecans and uncooked Ramen noodles.
Set aside.
Mix vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and noodle seasoning.
Pour this mixture over first mixture and toss.

title: chicken italian
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Place sauce over chicken. Cover and simmer until done (about 30 to 45 minutes).

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix well all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Combine margarine and sugar in saucepan over low heat and stir until margarine is melted and mixed well with the sugar. Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Combine dry ingredients. Add to egg and sugar mixture. Stir in pecans.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and cut in squares.

title: breaded parmesan fillet
directions: Combine cheese, bread crumbs, pepper and paprika.
Dip frozen fish in evaporated milk.
Coat with cheese-bread crumb mixture. Place in a baking dish and cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking for approximately 10 minutes or until fish is easily pierced with a fork.
Serve immediately while it is hot.

title: no roll crust
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together in 9-inch pie pan.
In measuring cup, combine oil and cold milk.
Whip together with fork.
Pour all at once over flour mixture.
Stir with fork until all flour is completely moistened.
With fork and fingers, press evenly and firmly line pan.
For unfilled shell, prick all over with fork and bake in 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ham and vegetable cream soup
directions: Clean
carrots,
celery, potatoes and onions.
Cut into medium size
pieces.
Place all in pressure cooker on trivet. Place
ham on
top.
Add 2 1/2 cups water.
Bring to 10 pound pressure
and cook
minutes.	While
hot
blend all parts together and add salt and black pepper to taste.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken, bone (reserve broth).
Brown ground beef. Add all ingredients to 2 cups of chicken broth.
