Cook over low heat for 3 hours.

title: pumpkin walnut bread pudding with kentucky bourbon sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8-cup ovenproof casserole dish or mold with 2 teaspoons of the butter.
In a large bowl, whisk together the half and half, cream, eggs and orange zest.

title: fluffy citrus dressing
directions: In saucepan, beat egg; add sugar, orange peel, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low to medium heat until thick (about 5 minutes).
Cool well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Serve with fresh fruit as a dip.

title: tillie's salad
directions: Combine juice from pineapple with water to make 2 cups.
Blend in jello, sugar and marshmallows.
Cook until marshmallows are melted.
Cool and when partially set add pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts.
Then fold in cream or Dream Whip.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan or mold.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. This pie has the flavor of a pecan pie.

title: green rice
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Follow the directions on a box of Pillsbury Plus yellow cake mix, except reduce the water to 1/2 cup and add 1 cup of canned pumpkin and 3 teaspoons of pumpkin pie spice.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake as directed.
Cool; frost with ready to spread frosting, mixed with 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon. Decorate with candy pumpkins.

title: grilled pork tenderloins
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a shallow dish or heavy duty Ziploc plastic bag.
Add pork.
Cover dish or seal bag and refrigerate 8 hours, turning pork often.

title: date bread
directions: Mix all together and bake one hour in moderate oven.

title: my queen of icing
directions: Cook all ingredients (except egg whites) together until it "spins a thread".
Beat
the egg whites until they stand in peaks. Pour cooked
syrup
mixture
over	egg whites and beat well. Then frost cake.

title: crock-pot soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except macaroni and cheese.
Cook low for 6 to 8 hours.
Turn to high and add macaroni and cheese.
Cook about 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot mac and cheese
directions: Spray crock-pot with Pam.
Drain macaroni.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Add extra cheese on top.
Cook 2 1/2 hours on low.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Crush the Ritz crackers; sprinkle over the mixture.
Melt margarine; pour over crackers. Sprinkle poppy seed lightly.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: alfredo light
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic, and saute until golden brown.
In a small saucepan, stir together milk, chicken broth, flour, salt and pepper over low heat until smooth and thick.
Stir into onion mixture.
Continue to cook over medium low heat, stirring frequently, until the sauce is thick.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Arrange salt and peppered chicken in a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Drizzle butter over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Drain off most drippings and blend with soup, milk and cheese.
Place broccoli around chicken.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Serves 2.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 325° until top is golden brown, approximately 25 to 35 minutes.

title: lobster canapes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cream butter and cheese together.
Stir in egg yolk, sherry, cayenne and Worcestershire.
Add lobster meat and mix well.
Top each bread round with spoonfuls of lobster mix. Bake on cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in molasses, sugar, salt, orange peel, caraway seed and rye flour.
Blend.
Then mix in white flour.

title: asparagus with shrimp sauce
directions: Heat half and half to boil in small saucepan over medium heat. Toss flour with cheese and add to half and half; cook, stirring until smooth.
Add cayenne.
Blend small amount of sauce into yolk; add back to pan, stirring constantly.
Heat to hot, but do not boil.
Fold in shrimp.
Serve over asparagus.

title: rhubarb raisin pie
directions: Prepare rhubarb.
Mix together sugar, flour and egg. Add rhubarb.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Spoon in filling. Put raisins around on top of rhubarb. Put top crust or lattice top.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing bake
directions: Butter one side of bread and cube pieces.
Beat eggs, soups and chicken in large bowl.
Fold in buttered bread.
Put in flat pan; cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove cover for the last 15 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water with bouillon until tender. Add pepper and cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted.

title: brown sugar icing
directions: Boil sugar and butter; cream sugar, butter and cream until a soft ball forms in cold water.
Add the vanilla and beat until of spreading consistency.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; mix well and set aside.
Trim crusts off bread; press each slice
to 1/8 inch with rolling pin or fingertips.
Spread each slice with a teaspoon of butter/onion mixture.
Place an asparagus spear on each slice of bread.
Roll up tightly and secure with wooden toothpick.
Brush rolls with melted butter and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove picks and garnish (if desired); serve warm.

title: crab amandine(60 pieces)
directions: Blend cheese and mayo; add onion and cayenne and mix well. Add crab; blend all together and spread on baked squares, leaving a higher mound in center of square.
Melt butter and add almonds; brown slightly.
Watch carefully.
Sprinkle on squares when cooled.
(Here you may freeze for 2 days.)
Bake at 400° on highest shelf of oven for 10 minutes.
Pass while hot.

title: liver fingers
directions: Slice frozen liver into "fingers".
Drench in flour seasoned with celery salt, paprika and pepper.
Fry in hot oil.
Cover with onion slices.
Turn when necessary.
Cover with tomato juice (approximately 2 cups).
Simmer.
Serve.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes, green onions and onion.
Mix together and add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve with chips.

title: spanakoriso(spinach and rice)
directions: Wash and dry the spinach, and tear into pieces.
Saute the onions, garlic and rice in olive oil until the onions are soft and golden; add tomato sauce, and stir.
Add spinach, bay leaves, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add broth, cover and simmer over low fire for 20 minutes.
This is normally served hot as a side dish, but it is also excellent cold.

title: creamy baked cheesecake(makes one 9-inch cheesecake)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In saucepan, melt margarine; stir in crumbs and sugar.
Pat firmly on bottom of buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Beat in Eagle Brand, eggs and salt until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched, about 1-inch from center. Turn oven off.
Spread sour cream on cheesecake.
To minimize cracking, return cheesecake to oven for 1 hour.
Chill.
Remove side of pan.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pecan date pie(makes two pies)
directions: Beat the eggs until foamy.
Add the sugar and syrup and other ingredients.
Add the melted butter last.
Bake the pies on a cookie sheet for about 30 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in a well-greased hot iron skillet at 400° to 450° until golden brown.
Remove from skillet as soon as it is taken out of oven.

title: green rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet and then add bell pepper, green onions, white onion and salt.
Cook until tender.
Add chicken and rice soup and water.
Let come to a boil.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Cover with water and salt, simmer about 45 minutes.
Add sliced potatoes, sliced onion, beans, tomatoes and sugar.
Cook for 45 minutes or until beans and potatoes are tender.
Remove bones from chicken, add corn, cook for 10 minutes.
Season to taste and add catsup and butter; stir well.

title: tid bits
directions: Mix and roll in small balls.
Bake on greased tin until light brown in moderate oven, about 18 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.
Watch carefully, they burn easily!

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Place into an oblong pan or 10 x 10-inch pan.
Pour Mrs. Richardson's sauce on top, add peanuts and let set in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: marinade for chicken, pork or beef
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate meat for 1 hour or more before cooking.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Crush cornflakes to make 1 cup crumbs.
Set aside.
In small saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Remove from heat.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Rinse chicken pieces.
Pat dry.
Brush with butter mixture.
Place crushed cornflakes or fine dry bread crumbs on a sheet of waxed paper.
Roll chicken in crumbs to coat. Arrange chicken skin side up and so pieces don't touch in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Do not turn.
Chicken is done when it is easily pierced with a fork. Season to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese cake supreme
directions: Let cream cheese
stand at room temperature to soften.
Beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and lemon peel.
Mix dry ingredients and gradually blend into cheese.
Add eggs and egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition just to blend.
Gently stir in whipping cream.
Turn into a crust-lined pan.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 55 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Cook
ground
beef
and
onion in a large skillet until meat is
browned,
stirring
to crumble meat; drain.
Stir in flour and
next
ingredients;
cook and stir for 1 minute. Stir
in soup.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Combine milk, cheese, mustard, salt and eggs in blender. Blend well. Fry and drain sausage.
Break bread into bite-sized pieces in large bowl.
Add sausage and liquid mixture.
Mix well with spoon and pour into 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan or casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: pineapple ritz
directions: Beat until stiff the egg whites; add sugar, baking powder, crackers and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix Dream Whip according to instructions (you may use skim milk).
Blend with vanilla, cream cheese and pineapple thoroughly.
Spread over cooled crumb crust.
Refrigerate for an hour or more.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch and sugar. Stir in boiling water. Let boil 1 minute. Then add butter and vanilla. Remove from heat when thick (not as thick as pudding). Serve over hot, buttered biscuits! Refrigerate leftovers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Brush over chicken, pork chops, etc.

title: old fashioned rhubarb cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and 1 cup sugar. Add egg; beat well. Combine buttermilk and vanilla; set aside. Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla to the creamed mixture. Stir in rhubarb. Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine the remaining sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: caramel puffin' corn
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add soda and vanilla.
Spray large pan lightly with Pam.
Put corn in; add syrup and toss.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in tight container.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer until chicken is tender. Remove chicken from broth, reserving 3 cups in Dutch oven.
Remove meat from bones and cut in pieces; set aside.
Add potatoes and carrots to broth; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add chicken, corn, tomato sauce and pepper. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, cornstarch and water 3 minutes.
Add Jell-O to hot mixture (no additional water, just Jell-O only).
Place strawberries in pie shells (can slice strawberries if desired). Pour mixture over strawberries.
Place in refrigerator to congeal, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Top with Cool Whip if desired. Enjoy.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Then mix egg, buttermilk and onion.
Mix all of this together and roll out in walnut size balls.
Drop in hot fat and cook until golden brown.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Melt the butter or margarine and add the water and uncooked rice.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes or until water disappears.
Add the milk and salt.
Boil for about 45 minutes or until milk is absorbed and rice is soft.
When cool, add the heavy cream (whipped).
Add the sugar and almonds.
Serve cold with thawed raspberries.

title: run for the roses pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until blended.
Stir in pecans and chocolate morsels.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: crunchy sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, 1/3 cup margarine, milk and vanilla in bowl; beat until smooth. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Mix flour, brown sugar, 1/3 cup margarine and nuts in bowl until crumbly. Sprinkle crumb mixture over sweet potatoes. Bake for 30 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: white chocolate chunk macadamia cookies
directions: Beat sugars, shortenings, vanilla and egg until light and fluffy. Mix with spoon and stir in flour mixture. Dough will be stiff. Stir in chunks and nuts. Drop by tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart. Bake 10 o 12 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable sandwich filling
directions: Chop vegetables fine and mix well.
Add 1 teaspoon salt. Drain on paper towels placed in colander for 1 hour.
Squeeze out any excess moisture.
Mix 1 envelope of unflavored gelatin with 1/2 cup vegetable juice that has been heated.
Mix whipping cream with mayonnaise.
Add gelatin and lemon juice.
Pour over drained vegetables and mix well.
Chill.
Spread on thin sliced bread. Better if it sets overnight.

title: super good rolls
directions: Place water in mixing bowl.
Beat eggs; mix into water with sugar and oil.
Beat with whip.
Add yeast and stir.
Add enough flour to make a sponge and beat really good.
Add salt and enough flour to make it ready to knead (not too hard).
Let raise once. Knead down and let raise again, then make rolls.
Let them get real light before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until done.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Trim dark green and pink parts from rind; cut in 1-inch cubes. Measure 7 cups.
Soak overnight in solution of salt and 1 quart water (it may take more to cover).
Drain; rinse watermelon rind. Cover with cold water.
Cook until just tender.

title: jalapeno cheese square(appetizer)
directions: Layer cheese and jalapenos into a 9-inch square pan.
Mix together eggs, milk and flour.
Pour over top.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool slightly, cut into squares and serve.

title: baked party chicken
directions: Wrap each piece of chicken in bacon.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with dried beef.
Lay chicken on top of beef.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mince onion.
Combine hamburger, onion, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, egg, and a little milk.
Make into balls and cook in oil. Remove meatballs with slotted spoon.
Add ketchup, 1/3 c. water, mustard, brown sugar, and Worcestershire sauce to pan and bring to boil.
Return meatballs to pan and simmer until hot.

title: eggless spice cake
directions: Put into saucepan, the sugar, water, raisins, Crisco, salt and spices.
Boil 3 minutes and allow to cool.
When cold, add flour into which has been sifted baking powder.
Mix thoroughly. Dissolve soda in boiling water (small amount) and add to mass. Put into an 8-inch square pan, greased.
Sprinkle granulated sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugars in a large bowl.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and baking powder; stir into creamed mixture with oats and chocolate chips, raisins and nuts.
Drop on lightly sprayed cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set and lightly browned around edges.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Pour dry gelatin over fruit and let sit for 15 minutes.
Add marshmallows and sour cream.
Fold in whipped topping; add nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, pineapple, whipped topping and nuts with the dry instant pudding; chill and serve.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Take off outer leaves of artichokes.
Cut off stem, leaving small end to hold artichoke together (save stem, chop finely and set aside).

title: leverpastej (danish liverpaste)
directions: Grind liver and pork together.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pan in a larger pan with hot water in a 350° oven for about 1 hour or until done.
When cold, slice and use for sandwiches.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble bread in bowl.
Add rest; top with cheese.
Let stand overnight.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook in heavy pan or double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Fill baked pie shell and cover with meringue from the egg whites (2).
Brown in 425° oven about a minute.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients and mix together in large kettle; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: plaza iii steak soup(a kansas city restaurant favorite)
directions: Melt margarine and blend in flour.
Add water and stir out lumps.
Saute ground beef and drain grease.
Add to flour stock. Saute onions and celery until slightly tender; add to soup.
Add mixed vegetables, tomatoes, beef concentrate, pepper and salt or Season-All.
Simmer until vegetables are done.
Freezes well.

title: drop in salad(ready in 15 minutes or less.)
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine the first five ingredients. Combine vinaigrette and lemon juice; drizzle over salad. Toss to coat. Serve immediately.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Jar and seal.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle layer of dry cake mix over peaches.
Layer butter pats evenly over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all wet ingredients well. Add all dry. Blend well. Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Great plain or add some Cream Cheese Icing.

title: weight watchers zucchini squash
directions: Cook together until squash is tender.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Place brisket in large Dutch oven; cover with water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender.
Remove meat.
Add vegetables, except cabbage.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add cabbage; cook until tender, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Add brisket; heat until hot.
Season to taste.

title: coconut yum cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on the box.
Take out of oven and poke holes with fork all over the top of cake.
Pour can of Eagle Brand milk and a can of cream of coconut all over cake.
Cool completely.
After cake is cool, mix some coconut with Cool Whip and spread on cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: baked fish in creole gravy
directions: Brown flour in bacon drippings until a rich brown.
Add celery, bell pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce and water, cook until smooth and the consistency of gravy.
Salt and pepper to taste Place well-seasoned fish on greased foil in shallow pan and cover lightly with more foil.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, covered, then remove foil, add tomato gravy and continue cooking uncovered 30-45 minutes longer.
Baste frequently with tomato gravy.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Sprinkle flour over cake mix.
Add Jell-O, oil, water and 1/2 cup frozen strawberries, thawed to mushy stage.
Mix thoroughly with electric beater.
Add one egg at a time, until all eggs have been added.
Bake in 9-inch pan at 350° for about 35 minutes or in tube pan at 325° approximately 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup to hard stage.
Take off heat. Add cinnamon and food color.
Pour into pan and break into pieces. Dip into confectioners sugar.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Fill saucepan with water and add carrots.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 to 6 minutes until tender.
Drain and dry completely on paper towels.
Return to saucepan.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion and meat in fat.
Add peas, tomatoes, catsup, salt and pepper.
Mix cornmeal as directed.
Put all ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Spread cornmeal mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 4 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat after 4 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Stir until melted. Add in Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat well; spread into greased pan (grease with butter).
Chill and cut into wedges.

title: holiday nuggets
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, margarine and sugar.
Blend in vanilla and almond. Gradually add flour and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Shape into 1 1/4 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten slightly with fingers.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and colored, crystallized sugar.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: c.m.p. cake
directions: Blend together margarine, flour and graham crackers.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and cool.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together. Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine all other ingredients with broccoli and place in 2-quart casserole dish. Top with buttered cracker crumbs and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mini broccoli pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, over high heat, in boiling water, cook broccoli and red pepper 3 minutes.
Drain well.
In small bowl, combine soup, garlic and Italian seasoning. Spread soup mixture over 12 muffin halves.

title: giant oatmeal-spice cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and spices; set aside.
Combine butter and sugar; cream.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: preacher's fried chicken
directions: Place chicken in bowl; pour buttermilk over and marinate 1/2 to 1 hour.
In another bowl, mix 1/2 cup of the flour with parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Remove chicken from buttermilk and roll in flour mixture.
Pour remainder of buttermilk in a buttered casserole dish.
Heat shortening and margarine in heavy skillet.
Brown chicken 4 to 5 minutes over medium heat.
Place on top of buttermilk in casserole dish.

title: pork chops in oven
directions: Combine margarine and garlic powder.
Dip chops in mixture and then coat with cracker crumbs.
Bake on lightly greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender and golden brown.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix in double boiler until chips melt.
Serve over plain cake while still warm.

title: ruby's freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt.
Soak 2 hours.
Pour off water. Mix sugar and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers and freeze in butter bowls.
Leave room for expansion of liquids.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat with hand mixer or blender.
Pour in greased pie pan.	Bake at 350° until done 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken terrific
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients.
Top with cheese.
Cover with stuffing mix, mixed with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes a 13 x 9-inch casserole.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine and boil for 1 minute.
Set aside.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all together and serve with chips.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, mixing thoroughly.
Add milk and soda.
Sift flour, cinnamon and nutmeg with a pinch of salt.
Add to mixture.
Pour in wine; dredge fruits and fold into batter with nuts.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes in 300° oven.

title: meatballs and ricesocorro, new mexico
directions: Combine meat, onion, rice and salt.
Form into 2-inch balls. Brown in hot oil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour mushroom soup diluted with milk over meatballs.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Serve with potatoes or over cooked rice.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, water, milk and syrup until soft ball forms when small amount is dropped into ice water.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and butter.
Stir while cooling pan in 2 to 3-inches cold water, until mixture starts to thicken.
Using a teaspoon, drop candy onto buttered waxed paper.

title: tiny tea biscuits
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together. Rub the shortening into the dry ingredients.
Add the milk and water.
Mix soft.
Pat out and cut.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ranchero baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients.	Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake 3 minutes at 400°.

title: omelet sandwich
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Line bottom with 8 bread slices, cutting them to fit.
Arrange cheese, ham and remaining bread slices over top

title: low calorie french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender for about 1 minute and then add 1 1/4 cup salad or Canola oil until thick and creamy. Adding oil last will keep dressing creamy.
Store in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted butter and sugar and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 7 minutes at 400° and cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and spread over cooled crust. Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Chill slightly and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: pink cherry salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: broiled steakburgers
directions: Combine ground round steak with all the ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Shape into 6 patties.
Place on broiler pan about 3 inches from broiler and cook for 4 minutes on each side.

title: chicken vegetable gumbo soup
directions: Melt butter in pot.
Add onion and cook until limp.
Add chicken broth, okra, cayenne, tomatoes and green pepper.
Simmer partially covered for about 1 hour.
Add rice, chicken and chicken gumbo soup and simmer about 1 hour.
Salt and pepper before serving.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix soup and water.
Stir in rice.
Place in large casserole or baking dish.
Place chicken dipped in melted butter on top. Cover and bake at 300° for about 2 hours.
Uncover and let brown slightly.

title: vegetable soup mix
directions: Cook beans and corn until almost done.
Fry okra; combine with all other ingredients and boil for 30 minutes.
Seal or freeze after putting into jars or containers.

title: seafood a la mediterranean
directions: To prepare shellfish, devein shrimp, leaving shell intact. Scrub mussels and clams well, discarding opened ones. Cut tail fins from lobster tails and leave meat in shell. Cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: *To sour milk, put 1 teaspoon lemon juice in it and let stand 5 minutes.

title: pineapple surprise
directions: Drain pineapple; mix with sugar, flour and cheese. Put in 1-quart Pyrex dish. Melt stick of butter. Crush crackers. Mix crackers with melted butter. Spread evenly on top of pineapple mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: beef marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stab both sides of meat (rump or chuck).
Sprinkle with meat tenderizer.
Place meat in baking dish or bowl.
Pour marinade over meat.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. Grill meat 1/2 hour on each side.
Baste while cooking.

title: squash puppies
directions: Slice and cook squash about 2 minutes or until tender.
Drain. Mash and drain again.
Combine squash and remaining ingredients. Drop mixture by scant tablespoon into hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix cocoa with hot water; set aside.
Blend flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder; set aside.
With electric mixer, beat Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla; add set-aside ingredients. Stir well.
Place batter in 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in butter to suit yourself.
Slice potatoes very thin.
Put browned chops over potatoes in casserole dish. Chop onion and cook in leftover butter from browning chops.
Add 1/4 cup milk and can of cream of mushroom soup to onion mixture. Let simmer until well blended.
Pour over chops and potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or microwave 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter and cornflake cookies
directions: Crush
corn
flakes.
Mix
well
with white Karo syrup, sugar and
peanut
butter.
Press
firmly in a lightly greased pan or oblong
baking
dish.
Put in refrigerator until it is really cool or until it can be cut in squares.

title: not baked oat cookies
directions: Mix shortening, cocoa, sugar, salt and milk; bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet; let cool.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed. Pour 1/2 of mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, no more.
Cool for 8 minutes.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In medium skillet saute onion in margarine until golden; set aside. In a medium bowl mix eggs and milk until blended.
Add corn and muffin mix, mix well.
Spread cornbread batter into prepared dish. Spoon sauteed onion over top.
Spread sour cream over onion. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 35 minutes or until puffed and golden. Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: spicy hot cider
directions: Put all ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Heat on the stove and serve.

title: southern baked grits
directions: Bring water and salt to boil.
Add grits, 1/2 cup butter and milk.
Add eggs and cheese.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with sausage and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey-dijon dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cut in shortening with a fork or pastry blender. Stir in oil and buttermilk; add a little more flour if too sticky. Handling as little as possible to avoid toughness, roll or pat to 1/2-inch thick and cut with a glass or cutter. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until browned at 450°. Makes about 12 two-inch biscuits.

title: low-fat chicken and rice
directions: In skillet add oil; sear chicken 5 to 10 minutes each side. Remove meat.
Add all other ingredients.
Boil 5 to 8 minutes. Place chicken breasts on rice.
Reduce heat.
Cook for 20 minutes. Let stay on burner 10 minutes before serving.

title: crispy apple pie
directions: Cook on the stove 3/4 cup sugar, the apples and water until sugar melts.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Put the remaining ingredients on top of apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top, if desired.
Melt 1 stick of margarine; pour on top.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes, or until brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, mix all ingredients except 1/2 can Durkee fried onions.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle rest of Durkee fried onions on top.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients, nuts and raisins last. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cauliflower layered salad
directions: Break up lettuce and put in large bowl.
Break up cauliflower in small pieces and layer over lettuce.
Spread mayonnaise over cauliflower.
Add crumbled bacon and spread evenly over mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar over mixture and, lastly, sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Make the day before and cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Mix completely about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: zachary's play dough
directions: Cook all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, 4 to 5 minutes, stirring until mixture forms a ball.
Remove dough from saucepan and let stand on counter 5 minutes.
Knead dough about 30 seconds, until smooth.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Knead dough too while adding coloring.

title: *orange-glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Pare cooked sweet potatoes.
Arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole. In a small saucepan, stir together sugar, cornstarch, salt and orange peel.
Slowly stir orange juice into sugar mixture.
Add butter or margarine.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir for a few minutes.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° and serve.

title: marty's meatballs
directions: Combine sausage, turkey and oatmeal.
Roll meat into marble-size balls and broil 5 to 8 minutes.
Melt jelly in a large skillet at low to medium high temperature. Add barbecue sauce. Mix well.
Add meat balls.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve hot in chafing dish.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Shave off all but a 1/16-inch layer of fat from top (rounded side) and sides of leg.
Dig extra fat out of tail assembly and shave excess fat off bottom side.
Make small incisions all over lamb with the point of a knife; insert a sliver into each slit.
Massage oil all over surface of lamb.
To help it brown and to give it a subtle flavor, rub all over with soy sauce. Place, topside up, on rack in pan.

title: calico bean bake
directions: After browning the beef and cooking the bacon, drain fat, then mix all of the ingredients together. Pour into a 9x13 baking dish or into a crockpot. If baking in the oven, bake for 40 minutes at 350 degrees. In the crock pot, on low for 2 to 3 hours. It is much juicier if done in the crockpot. This is great as a meal by itself, or as a side dish at a B-B-Q.

title: checkerboard cookies(mrs. alfred j. orlidge)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Divide in half.
Add chocolate to the one half.

title: two minute fudge(microwave)
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Do not stir.)
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Mix together.
Add vanilla and nuts and mix together.
Put in freezer for 20 minutes or in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll rolls and bake in jelly roll pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with cheese and vegetables.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken and pasta, in stew pan or Dutch oven. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes. Skin and debone cooked chicken. Add to sauce and cook 25 to 30 minutes until tender. Serve over cooked pasta.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Wash and slice potatoes.
Place in baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.
The last 10 minutes, add shredded cheese of your choice.
When cheese has melted, remove.
These are really good.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour into ice cream freezer can. Add milk to mixture up to the "Fill line".

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well; bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 13 x 11 x 2-inch pan.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer jello, boiling water and strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil water and sugar together 5 minutes.
Add tea, mint and allspice.
Cover and allow to steep for 10 minutes.
Strain.
Add fruit juices and boiling water and bring to boil.
Serves 12.

title: fun for the holidays
directions: You will need 1 pastry bag, 1 very small, round pastry tip (#1 writing tube), 1 mirror and 1 imagination.

title: busy day scalloped potatoes(microwave recipe)
directions: Place potatoes in 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Microwave Medium Low for 5 minutes.
Let stand while preparing sauce in a 4-cup glass measuring cup.
Combine half and half, American cheese and butter.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring often, until cheese and butter melt.
Stir until smooth.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes.
Stir gently and spread evenly.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir well.
Cover again with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on Medium Low for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle potato mixture with Cheddar cheese, parsley and paprika.
Microwave uncovered on Medium Low for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: steamed onions
directions: Peel onions and cut into quarters.
Put all ingredients into a pot with lid.
Steam over medium heat until tender.
Good with pinto beans, potatoes or any other vegetables.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind ham and pork together.
Mix all ingredients together and put in baking dish.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: festive layered salad
directions: Cook macaroni shell.
Drain.
Cool to room temperature.
Place lettuce in an even layer in bottom of 3-quart clear glass bowl. Arrange carrot sticks in an even layer over lettuce.
Cover with a layer of macaroni, then peas, onion and ham.
Sprinkle top with Swiss cheese.
Combine mayonnaise and dill in small bowl.
Mound the dressing in the center of the salad.
Arrange egg wedges around the dressing.
Cover.
Chill.
Just before serving, toss well to coat.

title: mama's egg biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center and add wet ingredients.
Knead and form a ball of dough.
Refrigerate one hour.

title: white coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Bake in a 9 x 15-inch sheet pan. Punch holes in top of cake while hot.
Bring sugar and milk to boil.
Pour over cake while hot; let cool.
Ice with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together butter, powdered sugar, 2 cups flour and salt like pie crust.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar, remaining flour (4 tablespoons) and lemon juice.
Pour over crust and bake another 20 minutes at 350°. Let cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chuck wagon western bean casserole
directions: Saute the hamburger until quite brown and separated.
Drain off any excess fat.
Add the beans and the other ingredients. Stir well, taking care not to mash up the beans in the process. Place in a 1 1/2-quart covered dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: holiday wassail
directions: In a large kettle, combine hot tea and sugar.
Add cranberry juice, apple juice, orange juice, lemon juice and clove.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Serve warm or cool.
Garnish punch bowl with orange slices studded with 12 cloves.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: quick broccoli and cheese
directions: Boil broccoli with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add cubed Velveeta.
Simmer until cheese has melted.

title: thai fried won ton
directions: In a bowl mix ground pork with minced white onion, garlic salt, minced coriander, fish sauce, egg, pepper and dash of m.s.g. Place about 1 teaspoon of pork mixture in the center of the won ton skin.
Fold over.
Bring the two corners around in shape of won ton and press corners of wrapper together (seal with egg yolk).
Fry in deep hot oil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Seve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: paul of manchester's chocolate oatmeal bars
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar and salt.
Blend in flour and oats until particles are fine.
Press 2/3 of crumb mixture firmly into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: luck o' the irish stew
directions: In a large saucepan, combine lamb or beef, beef broth, onions, pepper and bay leaf. Bring to boiling and reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Skim off the fat. Add the potatoes, carrots, dried thyme and basil. Bring to boiling and reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes more or until vegetables are tender. Remove bay leaf and discard.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Add all remaining ingredients. Simmer about 20 minutes.

title: josh's tiger bites
directions: In a 4-quart microwave-safe bowl, melt marshmallows and margarine on High 3 minutes, stirring after 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter until mixture is smooth.
Add Frosted Flakes, stirring until, well coated.
Press mixture into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Mix together the sugar and warm water until sugar dissolves. Add the remaining ingredients, using all the juices. Pour into plastic cup containers and freeze. Set out 1 hour before serving to thaw.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, mix well.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; mix well.
Add carrots and nuts; mix well.
Pour into one bread pan that has been greased and floured. Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: bourbon balls
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate bits.
While melting, roll vanilla wafers and mix with powdered sugar and chopped nuts.
Add bourbon or rum and white Karo syrup to melted chocolate.
Stir into chocolate mixture, wafers and sugar mix.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Heat oven 450°.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Heat skillet with small amount oil prior to placing batter in skillet. Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bridge creek heavenly hots
directions: Mix sour cream, eggs, flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in blender or processor until smooth.
Transfer batter to bowl. Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: german sauerkraut
directions: Boil sauerkraut in about 1-quart water.
While this is boiling, about 10 minutes, prepare the meatballs into balls and drop into pot with sauerkraut.
Cook about 30 minutes and then stir in flour paste to thicken.
Serve over mashed potatoes or as is.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Cut dough in slices (1/8 or 1/4-inch).
Arrange on pan.
Bake for 12 minutes at 375°.
Beat together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix berries with glaze and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Spread Cool Whip over the top.
Pan size:
10 x 15-inch or a pizza pan.

title: banana puff pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix together sugar, buttermilk, bananas and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into pie crust and freeze until firm.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cook tomato soup, Knox and cream cheese until smooth.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut bonbons
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar, butter and cereal in a bowl. Mix well and shape into small balls.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in a double boiler, mixing well.
Dip bonbons in chocolate and place on wax paper.
Let stand until firm.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: seafood mold
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Set aside.
Over medium heat bring soup to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatine until dissolved.
Set aside to cool.

title: cherry pinwheel dumplings
directions: Mix together.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread with generous amount of butter.
Drain 2 cans sweetened cherries and heat cherries with 2 cups sugar until dissolved.
Spread over dough.
Sprinkle a little cinnamon over all and roll carefully to distribute cherries evenly on dough.
Cut as for cinnamon rolls. Place cut side down in a well-buttered pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Then pour thickened and sweetened cherry juice over dumplings and return to oven for another 5 minutes or until slightly brown.
Serve warm plain or with cream.

title: great - special salad
directions: Sprinkle lettuce with small amounts of Blue cheese, carrots, celery, bacon bits, pecans, strawberries and red cabbage.
Pour dressing over.

title: chili
directions: In a Dutch oven pot, saute onions (1/2 bag).
Once cooked, add meat or turkey.
When meat is cooked, drain grease from pan.
Add sauce, crushed tomatoes and salsa.
Mix in 3 tablespoons of chili powder (more, if desired).
Sprinkle in garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer on low for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Can be frozen and reheated at will.
If you cook less meat, then omit the can of sauce.

title: easy chicken
directions: In a baking dish, place chicken in one layer on bottom; add salt.
Pour dressing over top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over mixture. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spidini bread
directions: Cut bread in 1-inch thick slices, stopping about 1-inch from the bottom.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix mustard and poppy seed with butter and onion.
Spoon butter mixture in between bread slices.
Place cheese in between bread slices.
Place bacon on top of bread.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes, or until bacon is done.

title: yellow cake
directions: *At 2,500 to 5,000 feet elevation, use 3 teaspoons of baking powder and at 7,500 feet, use 1 3/4 teaspoons baking powder.

title: pineapple oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and egg.
Cream and then add pineapple.
Sift dry ingredients and mix with creamed mixture.
Add nuts, dates and oats.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and crab bisque
directions: Cook vegetables in butter and garlic until crisp-tender. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add broth and cream.
Stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add crabmeat and heat through.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.

Add other ingredients. Grease bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with oleo. Pour mixture into dish and cover with desired topping (bread crumbs mixed with oleo or grated Cheddar cheese or melted oleo and crushed cornflakes).

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco mix together and set aside.
Use a 9 x 9-inch shallow dish or pan.
Spread refried beans over entire bottom; spread sour cream mix on top of beans.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over sour cream mix and sprinkle onions, tomatoes and olives on top.
Use chips to dip.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and cream cheese. After creaming well, gradually add sugar. Then add 2 eggs and start adding flour. Then alternate eggs and flour, ending with flour. Put in a cold oven and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add bananas, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350 F for 40-45 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Add pineapple to cheese.
Mix pepper, onion, garlic powder and salt into cheese.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Form into two large balls.
Cover each ball with remaining nuts.
Chill.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, tomato sauce and half of the onions together.
Place in pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Place remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over meatloaf and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: kramp special
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel and crumble.
Fry potatoes in bacon drippings.
When potatoes are done, add beaten eggs and stir until eggs are done.
Add can of whole corn and heat until corn is hot.
Serve with biscuits and jelly.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Melt together peanut butter and butter or margarine.
Combine all together and mix with the above.
Stir with spoon (not a mixer).
Spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: black bean salsa
directions: In food processor or blender, roughly chop the beans.
Be careful not to puree them.
Stir in all the ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with corn chips or sliced vegetables.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix enough cool chicken broth to make soft dough.
Roll real thin; cut in small pieces.
Cook in boiling chicken broth.
Stir lightly.

title: microwave fiesta pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in milk.
Add remaining ingredients, except salsa and sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch microwavable pie plate.
Cover loosely with wax paper. Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir edges of mixture into center. Smooth.
Cover.
Microwave 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve immediately with salsa and sour cream.

title: merry balls
directions: Dip each ball in this and let them dry on wax paper.

title: lucretia's legacy
directions: Mix
and
press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ranch style oyster crackers
directions: Pour over 1 or 2 (12 ounce) oyster cracker packages.
Mix well.
Bake in oven 20 minutes, stirring once during this time (oven at 250°).

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Peel zucchini; remove seeds and shred.
Mix zucchini and sugar; cook for 6 minutes.
Add pineapple and cook for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add jello.
Put in processed jars and seal.

title: chicken curry
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and margarine. Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs and pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, eggs and sour cream.
Stir in Jiffy mix.
Blend in melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.
Cut should come out clean.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add sugar to cranberries and let stand for 4 hours.
Add celery, nuts and pineapple.
Stir into jello that has partially jelled.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: low-fat chicken
directions: Coat each piece of chicken with sour cream.
Roll in cornflakes or Cheese Nips.
Lay in baking dish and spray with Pam. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Begin with layer of lettuce, as much as you want, depending on size of salad desired.
Then add layers of carrots, radishes, celery and green peppers, then a layer of mayonnaise, enough to cover salad.
Sprinkle with sugar and top with cheese and crumbled bacon.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook peppers and butter in skillet until tender.
Blend in soup, milk, chicken and pimentos.
Heat well and stir often. Serve over rice/toast.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, apples, oranges, orange rind and sugar; let stand for 1 hour.
Fold in the remaining ingredients.

title: zesty pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil and salt; drain.
Combine other ingredients and reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture.
Pour remaining over chops and simmer, covered, on low heat for 25 minutes, basting a few times.
Place chops on sheet and put apple on each. Cover with reserved mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef and onions; add other ingredients.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Season well with salt, pepper and paprika.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
In a large skillet, melt butter or margarine with oil.
Brown chicken well on both sides. Remove chicken to baking dish large enough without placing one piece on top of another.
Slice mushrooms and saute in 1/2 cube butter or margarine.
Add wine, soups and bouillon and simmer for 3 minutes.	Then pour this sauce over the chicken and bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown the hamburger and drain.
Add the spaghetti sauce mix and the tomato sauce and mix well.
Line an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 package crescent rolls.
Add hamburger mixture and sprinkle with package of Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Top with 1 remaining package of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a greased dish and bake 1/2 hour at 325 degrees.

title: baked eggs with mushrooms
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons butter in large skillet; add onion and mushrooms and cook until tender.
Add salt and Tabasco; remove to small bowl.
Cut bread into 6 rounds; spread with remaining 2 tablespoons butter and toast in same skillet.
Grease six ramekins.
Place one toast circle in each ramekin; top with a layer of onion and mushrooms.
Carefully break two eggs into each ramekin.
Top each with 2 tablespoons cream.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until eggs are set.
Serve immediately. Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna noodle hot dish
directions: Cook noodles as directed and place in large casserole dish (greased) and add rest of the ingredients.
Bake about 1 hour in 350° oven.
Canned peas and carrots may also be used and for low-cholesterol diets, use spaghetti or macaroni noodles.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large pot put olive oil, garlic, onions saute on medium heat until onions are soft. Add tomato paste stir. Add all other ingredients pouring them through a sieve or food mill into the pot. Cook over low heat for around 3 hours, stir.
Do not Cover. If meat is wanted cook and chop and add sweet italian sausage.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and pour over stuffing mix.
Boil chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Mix the soup and 2 cups broth.
In a 2-quart baking dish layer stuffing, then chicken, then soup and end with stuffing on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken with yogurt
directions: Remove chicken skin; cook chicken in 1 tablespoon margarine over medium heat until done on both sides.
Reduce heat; sprinkle with paprika, salt and dill weed.
Mix 1/3 cup water and dry bouillon; pour over chicken.
Add onion.
Cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 30 minutes.
Remove chicken; keep warm. Stir yogurt into liquid in skillet.
Mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup water; gradually stir into yogurt mixture.
Heat to boiling; stir constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour yogurt sauce over chicken; sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4 people.

title: chicken spaghetti #2
directions: Boil chicken in 6 cups salted water.
Remove chicken and add celery, onion and bell pepper to chicken broth.
Simmer until tender (30 minutes).
Remove vegetables from broth.
Broth should be 3 to 4 cups.
If not, add water.
Add to broth, the spaghetti and cook according to package directions.
Add deboned chicken, vegetables, drained pimento and cheese (cut in pieces) to spaghetti.
Stir gently until cheese is melted.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mixture thickens as it cools.
If allowed to cool, place in casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick, about 15 minutes.
Pour in shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: crabmeat fondue
directions: Melt together and serve with bread cubes.
Works well in a crock-pot after melted.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Cream together cheese and mayonnaise.
Drain shrimp and mash. Drain clams, reserving juice.
Mix all ingredients, except clam juice and gelatine.
Heat clam juice and Knox gelatine; dissolve. Add to shrimp mixture.
Pour in mold.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch, with aluminum foil or waxed paper; grease.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs in a small mixer bowl until very thick and lemon colored, about 5 minutes.
Pour eggs into a large mixer bowl.
Beat in granulated sugar gradually. Beat in water and vanilla on low speed.
Mix in dry ingredients gradually, beating just until batter is smooth.
Pour into pan, spreading batter to corners.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Blend cranberries, orange peel and celery (chopped fine). Dissolve sugar and jello in 1/2 cup water; add all other ingredients together.
Chill.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Add boiling water to Crisco, sugar and salt until Crisco melts.
Let cool; dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add yeast-water and beaten eggs to cooled mixture.
Gradually add flour to mixture and knead.
Place dough in greased bowl and let rise until it doubles in size.
Shape and put into pans.
Let rise until double again.
Bake at 400°.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown together ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Sprinkle in garlic salt, then drain.
Add Spanish rice, tomatoes and pinto beans.
Cook until thick.
Pour over corn chips, then add picante sauce and grated cheese.
Top with more corn chips.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: pepper steak
directions: Saute onion and pepper.
Remove from skillet and saute steak until brown.
Mix Heinz 57 sauce, gravy and tomato sauce.
Simmer on low for 15 minutes.

title: fish stuffed with shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread 1 tablespoon softened butter evenly over bottom of large pan.
Shell the shrimp.
Devein by making a shallow incision down their backs with a small, sharp knife and lifting out black vein with the point.
Drop the shrimp into lightly salted, boiling water and boil 3 minutes, until firm and pink.
Drain.
Chop coarsely and place in bowl.

title: fruit tart
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream the margarine. Add salt. Add sugar gradually. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add grated lemon rind. Sift flour.

Measure and sift together with baking powder. Add alternately to creamed mixture with 1/2 cup milk. Add chopped walnuts. Turn into well-greased bread pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Take from oven.
Place pan on rack and spoon the Lemon Topping over hot loaf.

title: chicken casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Bake chicken and debone.
Crumble chicken in large bowl.
Add soups and sour cream.
Crush crackers and coat with melted butter or squeeze margarine.
Layer casserole dish with one half cracker mixture.
Spoon chicken mixture over crackers and top with remaining cracker mixture.
Sprinkle top with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is bubbly.

title: beet hash(no dairy, low-fat)
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet; add vegetables and water.
Cook until crisp.
Add salt to taste.
Yields 2 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco seasoning and ranch dressing mix.
Stir to blend in.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat through. About 8-10 servings.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon and food coloring (if desired).
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 30 minutes. Cool and chill.
Spread with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired. Keep refrigerated.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening and beat well until creamy.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add sour milk, flour, soda, salt, mashed bananas and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: breaded turkey slices
directions: In shallow bowl, beat eggs and milk together.
In another shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs and salt.
Dip turkey slices in egg mixture and then coat with crumb mixture.
In a large skillet, melt butter and brown turkey for approximately 2 minutes on each side or until juices run clear.

title: franca's spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop onion, celery, basil and parsley into very fine pieces. Saute the veggies in 4 tablespoons oil until golden.
Add the ground beef, then add tomato sauce and paste.
Fill one tomato sauce can and the tomato paste can with water, then pour into pan. Add chicken bouillon to taste.
Stir often over a medium heat, adding some black pepper.
Sauce should be fairly thick, not runny. Is enough to cover 2 pounds of pasta.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour broth over chicken. Spread soup over chicken and broth. Slice eggs over soup. Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste. Mix melted butter, flour and milk together; pour over soup and eggs.
Spread evenly. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown crust forms.

title: amish cookies
directions: Mix oil, shortening, sugars and eggs and vanilla in a large bowl.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in sugar and press down on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, adding baking powder with last cup of flour.
Beat well after each addition.
Beat in flavoring.
Pour batter in greased and floured tube pan and place in cold oven.
Turn oven on to 350° and bake cake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check cake after 50 minutes for doneness.

title: punch
directions: Mix in 1 gallon milk jug and fill to top with water.
Freeze.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook syrup, water and sugar until it threads.
Add peanuts (raw). Cook until peanuts are done.
Add soda and butter.
Cook just a few stirs. Spread on a greased pan and cool.

title: elvis presley pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° if crusty outside is desired. Start in cold oven if softer outside is desired.

title: super easy cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Roll into ball and roll into pecans.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips.
Brown chicken with garlic and butter.
Combine juice from pineapple chunks with water, vinegar, brown sugar and gravy mix.
Add mixture to chicken.
Stir in green pepper; cut into strips.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Stir in pineapple and serve.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook on medium heat for 2 hours.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients with milk to desired consistency.
Drop by spoon in deep fat.
Excellent with fish.

title: easiest stuffed peppers
directions: Parboil peppers, then stuff with mixture.
Pour 1 small can of tomato sauce over them.
Cook in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grilled eggplant and peppers with fontinella cheese
directions: Cut eggplants in half lengthwise.
Cut peppers in quarters. Core and seed.
Combine oil and vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.
Marinate peppers and eggplant in oil mixture for 2 hours.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 sauce for top.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: caramel bread pudding
directions: Place brown sugar in top of double boiler.
Add bread cubes. Beat eggs.
Add vanilla, salt and milk.
Blend.
Pour over sugar and bread, but do not stir.
Cover and cook 1 hour over medium heat.
After 1 hour, remove from heat.
Turn onto serving plate.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening, adding sugar gradually.
Cream until mixture is very fluffy.
Add eggs, beat mixture until light and fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; add to mixture alternately with milk until milk and dry ingredients have all been added.
Add vanilla.
Pour into three greased cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cube cooked turkey.
Cook linguini according to directions. Make white sauce.
In medium saucepan, heat oil; add garlic, celery, green pepper and mushrooms and cook until tender.
Add tomato puree, bouillon, basil and salt and pepper to taste. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: crunchy meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into 1-inch balls.
Bake in a 375° oven about 10 to 20 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Beat well after each egg, but don't overbeat. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Add alternately with milk. Add vanilla and mix well. Pour into floured cake pans. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 25 minutes. Turn onto racks to cool, then frost when totally cooled.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, peanut butter and butter.
Boil about 5 minutes.
Add oats.
Drop on wax paper.

title: panic
directions: In buttered 9-inch square
Pyrex dish, spread pie filling. Spread cake mix over filling.
Pour margarine over cake mix. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake in moderate oven until nuts are brown. Serve hot or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: beef mushroom stew
directions: Roll meat chunks in flour to coat each piece lightly.
Heat the salad oil or shortening in a heavy pan with a cover; brown the meat, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add the potatoes, carrots and onions to the meat.
Then add soy sauce and water.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Uncover and add cream of mushroom soup and lemon juice.
Arrange refrigerated biscuits over top; bake, uncovered, in a hot oven (400°) for 10 to 15 minutes or until biscuits are browned.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix together with hands.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet. These freeze well.
It is not necessary to thaw before baking.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Seven-Up.
Freeze.
Before serving, thaw mixture slightly and add 7-Up.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble, then drain.
Prepare 9-inch pie shell, premade or scratch.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle in shell.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma's mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in water, drain and mash.
Add other ingredients. Place in buttered casserole and dot with butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Yield:
15 large servings.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Spread the mixture on tortillas.
Roll them up.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Slice when ready.

title: dreamy apricot salad
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and water in a small saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar and gelatin.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit; set aside to cool.
Combine condensed milk and cram cheese, beating until smooth.
Stir in gelatin mixture, then nuts.
Pour into a 9-cup mold or any suitable Corning-type dish. Chill until firm.

title: zesty corn relish
directions: Blend all ingredients in glass bowl. Allow to marinate 4 hours, covered, in refrigerator.
Store in glass jar in refrigerator.
With a little imagination, you'll find you can't be without this flavorful cooking accompaniment.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Combine milk, sugar and soda.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add corn syrup and margarine.
Cook, stirring constantly, until it forms a ball in cold water.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat and spoon on wax paper.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, cocoa, sugar and salt and set aside. Combine milk, vanilla and oil and mix until smooth. Stir in walnuts and dry ingredients. Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: meat loaf with vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into loaf and bake at 375° for 3/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix in order and drop from teaspoon on greased sheet.
Bake 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pie crust for fried pies
directions: Mix well and let set overnight or refrigerate for awhile. Roll out and cut the size of a saucer.
Prick pies with a fork and dip in sweet milk before frying.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat oil in large skillet. Add onion and green pepper. Cook until onion is translucent. Add meat and brown. Pour off all fat. Add beans and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Stir occasionally; remove bay leaf.

title: fruitcake tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients and fill 6 dozen small individual muffin tins or cover a shot glass with aluminum foil. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 300°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt
the
ingredients	and add 1/2 cup nuts.
Butter a Bundt pan.
Cut 15 biscuits in fourths and layer in Bundt pan. Pour half of mixture on biscuits.
Layer the other 15 biscuits (cut
into fourths).
Pour
the remainder of the mixture onto the biscuits. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Mix all together.
Makes large salad.
Serve with hot salsa.

title: mini meat loaves and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine ground beef, egg, 1/2 can tomato sauce, 1/2 can Durkee onions, 1/2 teaspoon salt and Italian seasoning.
Shape into 3 mini meat loaves and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange potatoes around loaves.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 minutes.
Spoon vegetables around meat loaves; stir to combine with potatoes. Lightly season vegetables with salt and pepper, if desired.
Top meat loaves with remaining tomato sauce.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes or until meat loaves are done.
Top loaves with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: sun's up soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, gradually stir milk into soup; add smoked beef and cheese. Cook and stir until mixture is heated through, about 5 minutes. Serve over toast. Makes 4 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Heat to boiling point the molasses and shortening, then add spices and soda.
Next add baking powder and salt.
Add milk and flour alternately, then add beaten egg.
Pour into warm greased pan and bake in moderate oven (350°).

title: microwave french onion soup
directions: In
3-quart
casserole,
place	onions	and
margarine. Cover. Microwave on High 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes. Add broth, water, salt and pepper.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes. Ladle
into
serving bowls with 1 slice bread and 1/6 of cheese on top of each. Microwave bowls 1 minute to melt cheese.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes. Simmer while melting oleo.
When oleo is melted, add rice, stirring to coat rice.
When rice is coated and golden, add hamburger mixture and tomato sauce.
Stir.
Cook on low until rice is done and sauce is absorbed.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Recipe makes 1 dozen.

title: bernie's apple crisp
directions: Butter 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange apples in plate.
Pour orange juice over apples.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and butter (coarse crumbs).
Place on top of apples.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 375°.

title: ruth's one hour rolls
directions: Mix butter, sugar and salt in warm milk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
When milk is lukewarm, add 2 cups flour, then yeast, then 2 cups more flour.
Cover.
Let rise in a warm place 15 minutes.
Pinch off pieces the size of a walnut and place 3 in each section of a greased muffin tin.
(Use rest of flour to dip fingers in while shaping dough.) Let set until double, about 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Brush with butter and remove from tin immediately.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: In saucepan, bring 1 cup of water to a boil.
Add frozen cauliflower; cover and cook as directed.
When done, remove from heat and set aside, undrained.
Save 1 cup of cauliflower for garnish.
Put celery soup in a medium bowl and mix milk with it until smooth.
Pour soup in with cauliflower and remaining water in saucepan.
Add cheese and mix well.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring until it begins to boil.
Put soup into a blender a little at a time on medium speed until soup is pureed and no chunks are left.
Pour soup into a saucepan after all pureed and put the saved cauliflower in and simmer on low heat until soup is hot.
Pour into a soup bowl and sprinkle with parsley.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrot, celery and onion in medium serving bowl.
Mix mayonnaise dressing, sour cream, sugar, dry mustard and salt in small bowl.
Add to cabbage mixture.
Mix well. Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This should take about two weeks.
Cover with brown gravy and cook over a kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve 3,000 people.
If more are expected, add the two rabbits.
Do this only if necessary...as most people do not like hare in their stew!

title: skillet chicken and rice
directions: Heat the oil in a nonstick saut pan.
Add the onion, carrots, parsnips, garlic and ginger and cook until tender.
Let cool.
Mix well with the remaining ingredients and shape into patties.
If too wet, add flour to shape.
Grill, broil or saut.
Serve on buns with the usual condiments.

title: spaghetti squash primavera
directions: Cut squash lengthwise in half and remove seeds.
Boil until poked easily with a fork, about 20 minutes.
Cool and scoop squash out into a bowl.
Toss squash with butter and Parmesan.
While squash is cooking, cook veggies, then toss with the squash after it has been cooked and cooled.
Saute mushrooms and toss them in.
You can put all this in a greased casserole and sprinkle with cooked bacon.
Heat at 350° until adequately warmed.

title: jumbo blueberry cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, stir in nuts and then add blueberries.
Using 1/3 to 1/2 cup batter for each, drop into ungreased baking sheets, about 6 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 14 cookies.

title: parmesan baked potatoes
directions: Pour butter into a 13 x 9 in. baking pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over butter.
Place potatoes with cut side down over cheese.
Bake uncovered at 400°
for 40 - 45 minutes or until tender.
8 servings.

title: wassail(hot apple cider)
directions: Mix and place into crock-pot or saucepan.
Cook low for 4 to 5 hours and enjoy!
Smells great and tastes even better!

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and boil exactly 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oleo, vanilla and red food coloring.
Stir by hand for about 15 minutes.
Spoon onto waxed paper to let set.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Drain all the juice from canned blueberries and pineapple into a 1-quart measuring pitcher and add enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Set fruit aside.
Heat the 2 cups liquid and pour into jello.
Dissolve jello completely.
Then stir in 2 cups cold water.
Cool jello a bit.
Then add blueberries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a dish.
Place jello into refrigerator and let set.
Prepare Dream Whip and beat in softened cream cheese mix on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Boil together the pineapple and sugar for 1 minute. Add the Jell-O. Boil 1 more minute and remove from heat.
Stir in the cream cheese. Freeze the can of evaporated milk for 2 1/2 hours. Beat and fold into mixture. Refrigerate.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and soup.
Pour half in buttered casserole.
Put half onion rings on top.
Add rest of beans and top with remaining onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: reuben spread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve on small cocktail rye bread.
Use small baking dish, glass pie plate or any shallow container.	May be reheated in microwave.

title: macaroni and cheese supreme
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Melt shortening.
Blend flour, salt and pepper.
Heat until bubbly. Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Place macaroni and cheese in alternate layers in greased baking dish. Cover with sauce.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and dot with butter (optional).
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes

title: chicken enchiladas(mexican)
directions: Cook onion in margarine; add water, flour and bouillon.
Add sour cream, 1 cup cheese, chilies and chili powder.
Add chicken to half of the mixture.
(Save half of the mixture to pour on top.)
Fill each tortilla with some mixture; roll up and lay in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour rest of mixture on top; sprinkle rest of cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with a salad.

title: cheese cake tart
directions: Lightly oil 9-inch tart pan.
In food processor or blender, process cookies and butter until mixture is crumbly.
Press mixture on bottom and sides of tart pan; refrigerate.
Preheat oven at 325°.
Blend cheese, egg white, vanilla, almond extract and honey in food processor until smooth.
Spoon filling into tart shell and bake until firm, about 30 minutes.
Chill and garnish with fresh fruit before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add oil and stir well.
Add eggs, one at a time.	Add carrots and blend well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50	minutes
in
a	9
x 13-inch pan.
Ice with a cream cheese icing.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Rinse spinach real good. Remove coarse stems.
(I used 1/2 bag of spinach in "salad section.")

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Brown chops in large ovenproof skillet. Pour off any excess fat.
Remove chops from pan and spread rice over bottom of skillet.
Return to heat and, stirring constantly, brown the rice.
Add water, 1 teaspoon salt, chopped onion, tomatoes and juice and corn.
Arrange chops over rice.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Simmer, covered, on stovetop until rice is done, 25 to 35 minutes, or cook in 325° oven until rice is done.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Add the oil.
Stir in the oyster crackers.
Let sit uncovered until the oil is absorbed.
Great boat snack.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix and press into an 11 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together; roll in small balls.
Bake at 350° to 400° until light brown.

title: papaw's cool grape jelly
directions: Boil first 2 ingredients according to Sure-Jell directions. Add sugar and boil 3 minutes. Cool, jar and freeze.

title: johnny's corn bread
directions: Heat oil in iron skillet and pour into mixture.
