Pour into skillet and bake one hour at 350°.

title: homemade "deli" pimento cheese spread
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature.
Add pimentos; mash with fork until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill before spreading on bread or toast.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Fry meat.
Add salt, pepper and olives.
Place 6 tortillas in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Add 1/2 the meat mixture to tortillas.
Pour 1 can enchilada sauce over meat.
Top with 1/2 the grated cheese.
Repeat.
Top with cheese.
Cover; bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brownies for the microwave
directions: Grease an 8-inch round microwave-safe baking dish.
Set it aside.
Place the chocolate and butter in a microwave-safe bowl. Cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir until mixture is smooth. Stir in sugar until well blended.
Stir in the eggs and vanilla until blended.
Add the flour, baking powder and salt until well blended.

title: hog head cheese
directions: Trim all meat from the head and soak overnight in salt water. Cook this meat along with hearts, tongues, feet and trimmings, not used in sausage.
When meat comes readily from the bones, dip off liquid and chop the meat fine.
Return meat to kettle; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cover with broth and boil 15 minutes. Then pour the mixture into a shallow pan.
Cover with cheesecloth and weight down.
Slice and serve cold with no further preparation.

title: baked turkey salad
directions: Combine turkey, celery, pecans, pimentos, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and cheese.
Turn into lightly greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Top with crushed potato chips and sprinkle with 1/4 cup chopped pecans.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lime jello
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Add pieces of cream cheese last.
Can also add nuts, if you like.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Beat egg in a bowl; add cubed bread, then crabmeat and seasonings. Stir; add butter and juice last.
Turn into greased dish.
Dot with butter and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: eggplant elegant
directions: Peel and cube a large eggplant into 1-inch pieces.
Cook until tender in as little water as possible about 5 minutes.
Stir frequently to cook all the cubes.
Remove from heat; add butter, grated onion, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend all ingredients and add crumbled crackers, until all moisture is absorbed.
Place mixture in a greased 1-quart baking dish; cover with grated cheese and bake
in 400° oven about 20 minutes, until thoroughly heated and cheese is slightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: taco pie
directions: Separate dough and place as crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan, ungreased.
Put layer of corn chips to cover; layer of meat, sour cream, cheese and more chips.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Serve with salsa and torn lettuce.
Can be made ahead and baked next day.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Add extract.
Alternately add flour and whipping cream.
Pour in well greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: popover pizza
directions: Note:
Can use Hunt's Manwich for quick sauce.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour half of the cake mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 12 minutes, using oven temperature on box.
Heat caramels, margarine and milk over low heat; spread
on top
of
baked cake. Sprinkle chocolate chips over caramel mixture;
top
with
remaining
cake batter.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cool completely and serve.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O
in
hot water or juice.
Stir in other ingredients.
Put in large or 14 small molds. Serve on lettuce or surrounded by cantaloupe slices.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat with mixer until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Set aside.
Boil milk, add yeast mix, put Crisco and milk in bowl with potatoes.
Then add salt and sugar.
Mix in 2 cups of flour, mix well, then add rest of flour.
Put out on floured board.
Knead until not sticky.
Put in large greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Then next morning set out and let them rise.
Then bake at 350° until brown.

title: mushroom dip
directions: Chop mushrooms; saute in butter.
Add 1 pack of cream cheese to blender.
Blend together.
Add salt and garlic powder to taste. Serve with crackers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place crescent rolls on bottom of pan.
Put cooked sausage over rolls.
Pour eggs and cheese mixture over sausage and rolls. Bake until golden brown.

title: mulligan
directions: Simmer diced onion, carrots and celery in small amount of water until almost done.
Add diced potatoes and continue cooking until all is done.
Add meat (cut into small pieces) and stir in enough gravy to moisten.
Continue simmering until meat is warmed through.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy black bean salsa
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving juice.
Cut up tomatoes; place in a bowl.
Add juice and all remaining ingredients; stir until combined.
Cover and store in the refrigerator.
Serve with tortilla chips or as an accompaniment to Mexican food.
Yield: about 4 cups.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: hamburger baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion together in pan.
Cook slowly until meat turns white; drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put into casserole dish; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a pot, cover with water and simmer until chicken is done.
Remove chicken and debone, cut in small pieces, set aside.
Add noodles to boiling broth, cook until almost done then add cut up chicken, stir until chicken is heated through and serve.

title: cherry tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix sugar, water and oleo in small pan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from fire and set aside.
Put 1 tablespoon cherry pie filling in each tortilla and roll up like a jelly roll.
Place in a baking dish and pour the sugar, water and oleo over the tortillas. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with or without vanilla ice cream.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Spread bread cubes evenly in an 8-inch round or square glass baking dish.
Sprinkle evenly with brown sugar, nutmeg and salt. Measure milk into 1-quart measuring cup; add margarine.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and quickly stir in eggs until mixed well.
Pour over bread cubes.
Do not stir.
Microwave at 70 percent power for 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground meat.
Add beans to warm.
Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine 1 cup mashed berries, sugar and cornstarch that has been dissolved in 1/2 cup water. Add 4 drops of red food coloring. Cool, then add remaining berries to pie crust. Garnish with Cool Whip when serving.

title: jiffy cookies
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring cocoa, sugar, margarine and milk to a boil.
Boil rapidly for one minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, then stir in oats.
When well mixed, drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Allow to cool and set.

title: baking mix
directions: Blend together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Store in an airtight container.
Use this when your recipes call for a commercial mix like Bisquick.

title: string beans with sesame dressing
directions: Put grated zucchini in a strainer over a bowl; sprinkle with salt.
Leave for 1 hour or longer to allow moisture to drain off. Squeeze excess moisture out before cooking; pat with paper towels so zucchini is as dry as possible.
Heat oil in a heavy pan; cook zucchini with the sugar over moderate heat, stirring until tender, but not too soft.
This will only take a minute or two.
Add lemon juice; raise heat a little.
Sprinkle with herbs; toss well. Spoon into a serving dish.
Add black pepper; sprinkle with extra parsley and herbs.
The zucchini can also be mixed with yellow squash ... mmmm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hello dollys
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Crush graham crackers and put in margarine, making a crust.
Add layer of chocolate chips, a layer of coconut and a layer of nuts. Pour milk over this.
Heat until it bubbles, about 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all but cheese together.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into greased pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over it.
Add remaining mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: toffee bits cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together the flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add eggs; blend thoroughly. Gradually add flour mixture, beating well.
Stir in Skor English toffee bits.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes, or until lightly browned. Cool about 1 minute, then remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chicken curry with bamboo shoots
directions: Cut makrut leaves in half and slice chilies into strips. Slice chicken breasts into pieces 1/2-inch wide.
Cut wings apart at joints.
Cut lemon grass into 2-inch lengths and crush with a cleaver.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in bowl.
Add egg yolks, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add chopped prunes.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 to 75 minutes.

title: brownie sin
directions: Grease 2 (9-inch) round cake pans. Line with waxed paper, extending up the sides and grease. Prepare brownies using directions on package for cake-like brownies. Pour mixture into pans. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.

title: old fashion potato salad
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Cut potatoes in small pieces.
Saute onions in microwave for about 2 minutes.
Add to potatoes.
Cut eggs in small pieces over potatoes.
Add salt and pepper and sprinkle vinegar.
Mix well.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix all ingredients together and layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: In large bowl, mix together sugar, salt, pepper, lemon juice and dillweed.
Stir sour cream into mixture.
Fold in onion and cucumbers.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Because salt draws liquid from cucumbers and will make the dressing too thin, I like to slice the cucumbers into a bowl of ice water and a little salt and allow it to sit for about an hour.
Then all liquid is drained off and the cucumbers are added to the dressing.
This makes the cucumbers crisp and the dressing stays the right consistency.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini.
Toss with dressing and rest of ingredients. Chill the salad and serve as a main luncheon dish or side to a dinner.

title: scripture cake
directions: Look up the references in the Old Testament.

title: fake pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients except pie shell in a mixing bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup Italian soup, beef, soup mix, bread crumbs and egg thoroughly. In medium baking pan, shape firmly into 8 x 4-inch loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until meat loaf is no longer pink (160°). Mix 2 tablespoons of drippings, remaining soup and water. Heat through. Serve with meat loaf.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salt water until tender (do not overcook).
When carrots have cooled, alternate peppers and onions.
Beat remaining ingredients and pour over vegetable. Cover and refrigerate.
Can be prepared week ahead of time.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: polish pierogi(cheese and potato)
directions: Cut margarine into flour.
Add eggs (beaten), cold water and salt.
Knead dough until soft and elastic.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll out fairly thin on floured board.
Cut out 2-inch circles with cup or glass dipped lightly in flour.
Fill each circle with filling.

title: rice pie
directions: Make deep slits in beef roast and insert garlic.
Mix salt and pepper.
Roll roast in salt and pepper mixture.
Place roast on grill over hot coals.
Cover.
Barbecue 30 minutes.
Add wet bay leaves to coals and cover.
Barbecue 15 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook chicken until tender, cut in small pieces.
Beat eggs until light, add milk and add with toast to chicken.
Mix well. Bake in shallow, greased pan for 30 minutes.

title: snappy turtles
directions: In a small bowl, combine 1 cup of frosting, crumbs, corn syrup and vanilla at low speed.
Beat 2 minutes at lowest speed.
Set aside.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Roll in flour; brown in hot fat until brown on all sides.
Add 2 cups water and simmer from 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: flan
directions: After caramelizing sugar, put over medium heat and stir until it gets light amber color, then take off stove.
Mix other ingredients together.
Pour over caramelized sugar; cover.
Set in pan of water and bake covered for 1 hour at 325°.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 90 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil for 1 minute.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 cup pecans or other nuts if desired.
Pour over cake immediately as it comes out of oven.

title: frazlianne
directions: Fry beef, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Add cooked spaghetti, corn, soup, olives and cheese; mix.
Place in oblong casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch and mix well. Add 1/2 cup of milk and stir until the sugar and cornstarch are dissolved.
Stir in remaining milk; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine and vanilla extract.
Let chill about 3 hours, then ready to serve.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, add berries, stirring occasionally until thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 the mixture into 8 x 8 x 2 pan or jello mold.
Chill until firm. Spoon sour cream over chilled jello spreading an even layer.
Pour remaining jello over top and chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: pink fluff
directions: Drain pineapple. Put cottage cheese, Cool Whip and dry Jell-O in bowl and beat. Then add pineapple. Refrigerate.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Flatten hamburger out to make a patty the size of a small plate.
Dice potato and onion; add salt, pepper, cheese and catsup.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°.
Clip hole in end of foil and drain.
Serve with a side salad, if desired.
No cleaning up, just throw away foil and dishes are done.

title: beer battered squash
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and beer.
Batter will be thick. Slice squash thin, dip into batter, drop into hot grease and fry until golden brown.

title: lime pickles
directions: Soak the cucumbers after slicing in thin slices in a mixture of 1 1/2 cups lime to 1 gallon water, making enough to cover the cucumbers.
Let them soak on lime mixture overnight.
Drain and soak for 5 hours in fresh water, changing hourly.
Make a syrup of the sugar, vinegar and spices and bring to a boil.
After changing the water for the last time, pour the syrup over the cucumbers and let stand overnight, then boil for 1 hour and seal in jars.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well.
Spread half of mixture in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with drained chilies and cheese.
Spread rest of mixture over top.
Bake in a hot 400° oven for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: sausage and spaghetti
directions: In a skillet, lightly saute links with peppers or mushrooms. Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.	Beat whites stiff and add 2/3 cup sugar (taken from the 2 2/3 cups).
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy. Add egg
yolks.
Add
flour
and
1/2 cup milk.
Beat well, then add egg
whites
and
vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.
Makes a large cake.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, molasses, oil and spices and beat well. Dissolve baking soda in the hot water and add to mixture.
Sift in flour and beat well.
Add boiling water and beat lightly and quickly.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: nestle quik cake
directions: Sift together sugar, Nestle Quik, flour and the cinnamon. Bring margarine and water to boil.
Add to dry ingredients with eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: curry dill dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover.
Blend on high speed until smooth.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with fresh vegetables. Yields 2 cups.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Mix together and spread on a Ritz cracker or saltine.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly; heat Crisco in skillet and fry on both sides until brown.

title: strawberry cake and icing
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients. Add the next 3 ingredients and 1/2 cup mashed strawberries; mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 pan. Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center will come out clean.

title: veal cutlets with artichokes & peas in lemon(piccata di vitello, carciofi e piselli al limone)
directions: Sauce:
Reserve
tablespoons
drippings
from frying cutlets; add butter
and garlic.
Blend well over medium heat. Add mushrooms and saute until tender.
Blend in wine, parsley, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Cook on low heat for 4 minutes. Add artichoke
hearts,
(optional
peas)
and heat thoroughly. Arrange cutlets on
platter
and
pour
sauce
over
cutlets. Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: one dish dinner
directions: Brown hamburger and onion soup mix together.
Stir in soup, water and mixed vegetables.
Pour into casserole.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss potato soup
directions: Put chopped veggies in broth and cook for 10 minutes or until tender.
Dissolve flour in milk; add to hot veggies.
Slowly boil. Shred cheese and slowly add to soup until melted.
This is thick and rich.
Great served with French bread.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Salt and pepper hamburger; fry slowly.
Drain grease.
Combine all ingredients and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients. Shape into balls. Place on baking pan. Bake in 300° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together taco seasoning mix and sour cream.
Layer all ingredients, beginning with refried beans, sour cream mixture, Cheddar cheese, tomato and onions.
Pour into square dish and dip with tortilla chips.
(Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch dish.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg thoroughly.
Sift rest of ingredients together and stir in above mixture.
Chill dough 1 1/2 hours.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour in crisscross design.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple juice. Add pineapple and nondairy whipped topping. Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Spread beef slices on bottom of baking dish.
Season chicken (with salt and pepper) to taste.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each chicken breast.
Place chicken on top of beef.
In small bowl, mix sour cream and mushroom soup; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and line bottom of casserole dish.
Heat soups and pour over chicken.
Top with dressing.
Pour broth over the dressing.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: winter treats no-bake snowballs
directions: Mix butters and sugar well.
Add cocoa and oats.
Mix until dough will form.
If it is too gooey, add a little more oats. Form teaspoons of dough into balls and roll in coconut. Refrigerate for an hour or until firm.
Makes 24 balls.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly (mix by hand); reserve one cup.
Pat remaining mixture lightly in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
While crust is baking, beat sugar, cream cheese, lemon juice and 1 egg until lightly smooth.
Spread over baked layer. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes longer. Cool; cut into bars.

title: new orleans shrimp salad
directions: Combine cooled rice with the next 8 ingredients.
Season to taste with salt and pepper, mixing well.
Chill for several hours or overnight and serve.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Place zucchini, onions and salt in a large bowl.
Mix well and cover.
Refrigerate overnight. The next day, drain well and rinse under cold water. Drain for 1 hour.
Place mixture in a heavy pot with remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes.
Cool and store, covered, in refrigerator up to 4 weeks; or fill 3 to 4 pint jars, seal and process in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Good as a topping for burgers, sandwiches and cold meats.

title: hard-boiled eggs
directions: Place eggs in saucepan just large enough to accommodate all. Cover with water right out of top.
Add the vinegar.
Bring to boil slowly over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Cool with running water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese.
Combine with softened margarine and sour cream. Add onions.
Shape into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chopped pimento or chopped green pepper may be added to taste.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water; stir and let cool.
Add cranberry sauce and sour cream; mix well.
Stir in oranges and walnuts.
Spoon mixture into 5 cup mold and chill until set.

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Put in large casserole dish.
Add slices of cheese on top of hamburger.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk to can of cream of mushroom soup and pour over top of mixture. Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: mud pie
directions: Pour a layer of chocolate syrup to barely cover the top of pie crust.
Soften ice cream until spreadable.	Spread over syrup in crust.
Freeze until it hardens.
Drizzle more syrup on top before serving.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Bring oleo, sugar and milk to a full rolling boil in a heavy 4-quart saucepan, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly, to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool. Cut into squares.
Makes about 6 pounds.

title: chess squares
directions: Pour over and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Be sure to cool before cutting into squares.

title: chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Beat eggs and sugar together, add next four ingredients and beat well. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes. Then reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make 3 holes in dry mix.
In one hole number 1, place vinegar.
In number 2 hole, place oil.
In hole number 3, place cold water.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 9-inch square or round pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together.
Serve on a lettuce leaf or use as salad.
Good in the summertime.
(Must refrigerate.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in baking dish.
In saucepan, saute (do not brown) onion in one stick of butter.
Add cream of chicken soup, sour cream and Velveeta.
When blended, pour over potatoes.
Top with cornflake crumbs mixed with one stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: leaner lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish with vegetable oil spray.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix well and chill for 24 hours.
Keeps for days.

title: mrs. smith's peanut butter icing
directions: Combine peanut butter, butter and vanilla; beat until light, adding milk.
Gradually add sugar.
If necessary, add more milk to be able to spread smoothly.
Especially good on chocolate cake.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Whip all ingredients together.
Pour into a graham cracker or vanilla wafer crust.
Chill 1 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Put soup in casserole; add milk and mix.
Add tuna, peas and 3/4 of crackers.
Stir all together.
Sprinkle top with remaining crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fudge icing quick
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until ready to spread.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: In large bowl, cream sugar and cheese until smooth.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Serve with purchased gingersnaps or apple wedges. Yield:
about 7 cups of dip.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with seasonings.
Place in crock-pot. Combine soup and milk; mix until smooth.
Pour over chicken. Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: potato salad with apples
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve cold.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Lay slices of Monterey Jack cheese on bottom of 2-quart rectangular casserole dish.
Split drained chilies and lay flat on top of cheese. Place slices of Cheddar cheese on top of chilies.

title: tater fried fish
directions: Lightly beat together mayonnaise, eggs, pickle relish and salt.
Dip fish into egg mixture, then into the potato flakes, coating well.
Fry in oil 5 to 10 minutes until crisp.
Turn and fry other side.
This makes 6 servings.

title: old-fashioned cheesecake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and let it cool some.
Then in another bowl, cream together cheese, sugar, vanilla, lemon juice and lemon Jell-O and mix well.
Then fold in whipped cream.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread pecans on a baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until fragrant.
Let cool and chop coarsely in a large bowl.
Stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.

title: english apple pie
directions: Beat butter and brown sugar until pale and fluffy.
Stir in flour, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and water until smooth and thick. Add pecans.
Mound apples in 9-inch pie plate. Mix sugar with remaining cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Spoon pecan topping over apples in dollops.
Bake on lowest rack at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until apples are tender when pierced.

title: scrambled egg brunch
directions: Fry sausage; drain well. Combine remaining ingredients and add sausage. Pour into well-oiled 9 x 13 casserole. Let stand overnight.

title: angel food fruit cake
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces (about one-inch) and spread in a 9 x 13 pan.
Mix pudding, milk and sour cream.
Pour over cake.
Let set for approximately 15 minutes.
Cover with Cool Whip and spread pie filling on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with potato chips, if desired.

title: chicken and artichoke casserole
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
In frypan, brown chicken pieces in melted butter. Transfer chicken to a shallow 3-quart casserole and arrange artichokes in between.
Set aside.
Drain all but 3 tablespoons drippings from frying pan; add mushrooms and cook until golden. Stir flour into mushrooms and cook 1 minute.
Then add broth, sherry and rosemary.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Pour sauce evenly over chicken and artichokes.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: low-fat zucchini pizza
directions: Sauce the zucchini slices in hot olive oil until translucent. Drain and set aside.
Cut the bread sticks in half, long ways and toast in the oven until just lightly toasted.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for about 15 minutes, then cool.
Combine and freeze next 3 ingredients in large container a day ahead. Take out of freezer 2 to 3 hours before using and let thaw gradually, breaking up with a fork.
Pour last 2 ingredients over mixture just before serving.
Punch will be icy.

title: quick and easy pork chop meal
directions: In Dutch oven, brown pork chops 2 to 3 at a time.
After all are browned, return them to Dutch oven.
Place potatoes, carrots, onions on top of chops.
Add tomato soup and 1 can water.
Add pepper and approximately 1 tablespoon parsley.
Simmer over medium heat approximately 30 minutes.
Add peppers and simmer another 30 minutes or until vegetables are cooked.

title: neiman marcus strawberry butter
directions: Whip butter in bowl of an electric mixer until fluffy.
Fold in strawberry preserves.
Return to refrigerator and allow butter to solidify.

title: chocolate hershey pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and candy bars in milk over low heat.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla.
Pour in baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: julie's chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken with salt and pepper. Remove skin and bones from chicken, when the chicken has cooked up tender, in a large pan, add broth from boiled chicken with 2 cans of chicken broth, add a tsp. of butter. Boil on medium heat. In a bowl, combine flour, eggs and water. Make sure the flour mixture is stiff. On a floured surface, roll out dough, cut into 2 inch strips or squares. Drop dumplings into boiling chicken broth. Stir gently with a fork between each rolling of dumpling. Add chicken, let set for about 10 minutes. Enjoy!

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in large heavy skillet; drain.
Add all ingredients, except cabbage and macaroni.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
If you prefer a thinner soup, add more water.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion evenly on bottom of lightly greased 10-inch pie plate.
Blend remaining ingredients in blender on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour over other ingredients in pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until golden brown and knife comes out clean from center of pie.
Serves 6.

title: taco beans
directions: Cook pinto beans in lightly salted water along with bacon drippings. When beans are almost done, brown the ground meat and drain. Mix into beans and continue cooking.

title: bean soup (crock-pot)
directions: In crock-pot, cook on low for five hours the first day.
Cook on low for one hour the 2nd day.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake as directed on package.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then poke with a fork.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and spoon over cake in pan.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease spring-form pan.
Crush 1/2 package of graham crackers and dust sides of pan and remaining crumbs leave on bottom.
Cream cheeses together on medium until mixed well.
Add remaining ingredients in order given, mixing until smooth and creamy.
Pour into pan and place in oven.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes, then when done baking do not open oven!!!
Shut oven off and leave cheesecake in the oven for 1 to 2 hours.
Remove and let cool completely.
Run a knife around side.
Remove side rim and cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with cherries or strawberries.

title: fluffy sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Beat eggs. Add sweet potatoes, condensed milk, butter, lemon juice, spices and salt. Mix well. Pour into 9-inch pastry shell. Bake 15 minutes at 425°. Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking 20 to 25 minutes.

title: squash and cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil squash and onion in small amount of salted water until barely tender.
Drain.
While squash is cooking, prepare topping.

title: swiss corn bake(serves 6)
directions: Cook corn in 1 cup salted water for 3 minutes.
Drain. Combine corn, evaporated milk, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 3/4 cup cheese.
Turn into a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Toss crumbs with butter and remaining cheese.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine cereal and milk.
Let stand until cereal softens.
Add egg and oil.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture and raisins if desired. Stir only to combine.
Divide into 18 muffin cups coated with cooking spray.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: moo's chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Saute chopped onion and green pepper in butter or margarine and combine.
Add all of the remaining ingredients together; simmer for about 20 minutes, or until desired consistency.
Serve topped with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Knead 5 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator for 3 days.
Knead 5 minutes on 2nd and 3rd day.
On 4th day divide into 5 one-pound rolls.
Bake at 175° to 200° for 4 hours, turning each hour.

title: myrtie's egg custard
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually stir in scalded milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Cool on rack, then chill.

title: amy's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first four dry ingredients.
Mix butter, vanilla and sugar until smooth. Beat in eggs to butter mixture.
Gradually add dry ingredients and then chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon curd
directions: Grate lemon peel on all 4 lemons.
Place grated lemon peel on sugar, then squeeze lemon juice out of all 4 lemons and pour over sugar.
Put butter in double boiler. Add sugar with the lemon peel and juice.

Let sugar melt over hot but not boiling water, stirring, then add beaten eggs, stirring constantly, until it becomes thick. Do not let boil or eggs will become scrambled. Pour into jars and cover at once.

title: low-fat potato bacon soup
directions: Spray a 3-quart saucepan with nonstick coating.

Add the chopped onions and bacon. Cook and stir over medium heat until onions are tender but not brown. Stir in water, chicken broth and potatoes. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Using a potato masher, slightly mash some of the potatoes. Stir in the evaporated milk, seasoning mix, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until heated through.
Ladle soup into bowls. Top with sour cream and chives, if desired.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat oil to 400°.
Mix and sift flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs, add onion and mix.
Add dry ingredients and beer alternately and blend lightly.
Using a tablespoon, drop mixture into hot oil and cook until done and as brown as desired, turning once.
Drain on absorbent paper and serve immediately.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Melt cranberry sauce and drain; reserve liquid and berries. Mix cranberry liquid, boiling water and jello.
Stir and add lemon juice and salt.
Chill.
Add mayonnaise and fold in apples and nuts. Pour in mold and chill.

title: apple surprise
directions: Layer in order one layer of each in 2-quart Pyrex dish.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour (more or less).

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients until they stick together easily.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate chips and wax.
Dip each ball in chocolate mixture.
Set on wax paper until dry.
Store in Tupperware.

title: creamy corn slaw
directions: Combine corn, onion, parsley flakes, sliced olives and grated carrots and toss with dressing made by combining remaining ingredients.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: keaton's blue ribbon cornbread
directions: Sift flour once, measure and add baking powder, sugar and salt, and sift again.
Add cornmeal and mix well.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Add shortening. Bake in well-greased corn ear pans or greased breadstick pans in hot oven at 425° for 20 or 25 minutes, or until done.
Makes 2 dozen corn ear sticks or 3 dozen short corn sticks.

title: jello jigglers
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, stirring until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Do not add cold water.
Pour mixture slowly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill for at least 3 hours.
(Jigglers will be firm after 1 hour, but will be difficult to remove from pan.) When ready to cut, dip bottom of pan in warm water for 15 seconds to loosen gelatin.
Cut shapes with cookie cutter all the way through gelatin.
Lift with index finger or metal spatula.
If Jigglers stick, dip pan again for a few seconds.
Yields 2 dozen. Cut recipe in half for 1 dozen.

title: cabbage and corned beef
directions: In a large Dutch oven, cook cabbage until almost done (approximately 20 minutes).
Break the corned beef into small pieces and mix with the cabbage.
Simmer until thoroughly heated. Serve with cornbread and pinto beans.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add juice and turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan to chill until partially congealed.
Fold oranges and pineapple into gelatin mixture.
Chill until set. Prepare instant lemon pudding mix, using 1 cup milk.
Whip whipping cream; fold into lemon pudding.
Spread on orange gelatin mixture and chill.
Serves 12 to 13.

title: vegetable medley casserole
directions: Cook all vegetables according to package instructions.
Drain well and place in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
In a saucepan, blend soup and flour.
Add tomatoes and stir until mixture boils.
Add cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Pour sauce over vegetables and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 10.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Put first 3 ingredients through food chopper.
Boil all ingredients together 1 hour.
Can.

title: maidrites
directions: Brown onion and hamburger.
Cook until brown.
Drain meat. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat 1 hour.
Serve on buns with pickles and cheese.
Serves 4.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 15 minutes.

title: apricot squares
directions: Mix all ingredients, except jam until dry and crumbly.
Mix well, using spoon and hands.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Line pan with
peaches.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, 1/2 cup sugar,
milk, oleo and vanilla.
Mix well by hand.
Spread over peaches.
Combine 1 cup sugar with water.
Pour over batter. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: end of garden pickles
directions: Soak all vegetables overnight in 2-quarts water with 1/2 cup salt added.
Cook for 10 minutes; drain well.

title: wild rice and ground beef casserole
directions: Wash rice by running cold water through in strainer until water runs clear.
Place rice plus 3 cups cold water and 1/2 teaspoon salt and bring to boil for 1 minute, then lower heat and simmer (keep covered) for 30 minutes, until rice opens.
Drain.

title: orange nut bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine oleo, eggs and sour cream.
Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Blend in orange peel.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in sour cream mixture.
Fold in walnuts.
Spread mixture into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and continue cooling on wire rack. Frost with Orange Glaze.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef. Drain well. Melt cheese in microwave and add tomatoes with green chilies. Stir well. Add meat to cheese mixture. Serve with Tostitos or Doritos.

title: banana split pie
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a dish and refrigerate while beating next mixture.
Beat powdered sugar, egg, margarine and vanilla 20 minutes.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Slice bananas over pudding mixture.
Top with pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Add nuts last. Pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° (for glass container, bake at 325°).

title: pizza snacks
directions: Place biscuits on cookie sheet.
Take a small juice cup and impress in each biscuit.
Spoon spaghetti sauce in each biscuit. Add pepperoni, then sprinkle cheeses on top.
Bake at 350° until edges are brown.

title: glorified rice
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Cook liquid over medium heat to boiling.
Stir in precooked rice and add salt.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in shallow casserole dish.
Make 5 cuts partially through loaf of Spam; add loaf in dish.
Drain fruit cocktail, saving juice.
Combine cornstarch and brown sugar.
Stir into juice and add margarine.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in fruit and simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon over Spam and sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, basting with juice during baking. Serves 3 to 4.

title: scallop chowder
directions: Boil scallops for 1 minute in chicken broth, then simmer and add milk and potato soup.
Mix thoroughly and stir in cream and snipped chives.
Heat to boiling, then serve.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Combine shortening, 2 cups sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix the 2 flours and add to the mixture alternately with 1 cup milk.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and lightly floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan or an angel food cake pan; sprinkle the bottom with nuts.
In a saucepan, melt the butter; add the brown sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and pudding.
Stir until it is mixed well.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a greased casserole, place the sliced potatoes in bottom. In a separate bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour the mixture over top of the potatoes.
Cover with lid.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover the potatoes and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Needs to set overnight.

title: chocolate sinclair cake
directions: Crush graham crackers and place in bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Mix pie filling, milk and Cool Whip.
Pour on top of crackers.
Put another layer of crackers and mixture.
Top with frosting.
Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: In a casserole, stir all ingredients except mushrooms.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Stir in mushrooms and bake 10 to 20 minutes more.

title: chickpea and tomato stew
directions: Drop the tomatoes into boiling water for 15 seconds.
Remove with a slotted spoon and peel.
Mince the tomatoes.

title: hot cheese rounds
directions: Blend flour and butter. Combine with cheese and Rice Krispies. Roll in small balls; flatten with a fork. Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cracker candy
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Line foil with saltine crackers.
Boil oleo and brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and pour chocolate chips over the top.
Spread chips when melted. Refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Cook rice per package directions.
After rice has cooked, mix with other ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon into a 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers thin. Slice onion very thin.
Toss with the sour cream, vinegar and sugar.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine 8 ounces cream cheese and 3/4 cup powdered sugar.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter and 1/2 cup milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Dribble with chocolate.
This is a frozen pie.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: cabbage deluxe
directions: Fry bacon and remove from grease, crumble and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients to pan drippings and cover to steam.
Steam 5-6 minutes until limp.
Add bacon on top of veggies and serve hot.

title: lemon sage dressing
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter.
Add celery, onions and carrots.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jen's chow-chow
directions: Coat pork with taco seasoning.
Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add pork and cook until brown.
Add salsa and preserves to pork.
Cover and simmer on low heat for approximately 30 minutes.
Serve over a bed of rice.

title: mashed potatoes for a crowd
directions: Boil peeled potatoes until tender; drain.
Mash potatoes with butter, cream cheese and sour cream.
Place in an ovenproof dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, topped with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: lasagna
directions: Step 1:
Boil noodles approximately 10 minutes.
Drain and place in cold water.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients in order listed until well blended.
Pour into greased casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour in 350° oven.

title: deer porcupines
directions: Mix deer, rice, onion and seasonings.
Form into small balls. Fry in hot oil (or bake in oven), turning frequently, until light brown, but not crusty on all sides.
Add tomato sauce and water. Mix well.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: richmond chocolate frosting
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Pour in boiling water.
Boil on stove until mixture thickens enough to spread. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; stir.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Heat water.
Melt sugar, salt, molasses and Crisco.
Add yeast to mixture when mixture is lukewarm.
(Too hot will kill yeast.) Add rye and white flour.
Knead until dough does not stick to board or
hands.
Put in pan and let rise to double in size. Knead down and divide into thirds.
Shape into loaves and let rise to double in size, then bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool on rack so air can circulate around bread.
Raisins can be added if you choose.
This bread has a strong molasses rye flavor.
It does not rise very high so don't expect a huge loaf.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Pour over cake and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix butter and eggs, then add dry ingredients and boiling water alternately.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In medium skillet, cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in salt, oregano, pepper, crumbs, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, onion and green pepper.
Pour into pie shell.
Spread Cheese Topping over filling.
Bake for 30 minutes. Cut into wedges.
Stir remaining tomato sauce and chili sauce together.
Serve with pie.

title: golden vegetable salad
directions: Mix ingredients well; serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: lemon kiss cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter, sugar and lemon extract until light and fluffy.
Add flour and almonds.
Beat at low speed until well blended.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour for easier handling.
Heat oven to 375.
Shape tablespoonful dough around each candy kiss, covering completely.
Roll in hands to form ball. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 for 8 to 12 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet and cool completely.
Lightly sprinkle cooled cookies with powdered sugar.
In a small saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips and shortening, stirring until smooth. Drizzle over each cookie.
Yield: 6 dozen cookies.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add measured liquid and lemon juice.
Measure 2 1/2 cups and pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill until set, but not firm.

title: mock eclairs
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed.
Cut cake into squares.
Cut each in half lengthwise.
Spread one tablespoon pudding between cake layers and top with chocolate topping.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: braided egg bread
directions: The secret of this pie is the light thin crust.
It's a much lighter treat than traditional apple pie.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all together and knead in a soft ball.
Roll out on a flour table and put in pie pans with fruit.
Bake 350 degrees until brown.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a pan; bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat. Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat well until blended. Pour into 2 greased 13 x 9-inch pans.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Combine strawberries, sour cream, half and half, sugar and vanilla in an electric blender; process until smooth.
Pour into individual soup bowls; garnish each serving with a strawberry fan or slices.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: chicken salad pita pocket
directions: Combine chicken, grapes and pecans in a medium bowl.
Mix together salad dressing, sour cream and lime juice; stir into chicken mixture.
Place lettuce leaf into pita pocket, then add chicken salad.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla, lemon rind and eggs.
Beat together until well blended.
Pour into prepared 9-inch graham cracker pie crust.
Bake just until puffed and center is dry, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Serve with cherry or blueberry topping.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix all together.
Cook for 30 minutes. Stir, then cook for another 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple spice cake
directions: Prepare apples and set aside.
Measure oil and put in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Beat until creamy.
Sift flour and measure.
Add salt, soda and baking powder.
Add small amount of creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
When all dry ingredients have been added and mixed well, add apples and nuts.
Mix well and then spread in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: moist pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix well. Fold in the pecans and raisins. Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Pour dough in pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: niko's quick chili
directions: Brown onions in vegetable oil.
Add hamburger and slowly reduce to get most oil.
In separate pan, brown chorizo and remove from oil.
Remove hamburger and onions from oil.
Discard all oil. Put all ingredients in large pot and simmer 45 minutes.
You don't need any other spices as the chili-hot-beans, Tabasco chile mixing and chorizo have all that you'll need.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix thoroughly, then make a pile with a hole in the middle. Into the hole pour a mixture of the vinegar and water, mixed well. Now work the dough until ready to roll.
Makes two 9-inch pie crusts.

title: layer shortcake(master recipe)
directions: Cream the butter with half the sugar; add remaining sugar gradually, then the well beaten eggs.
Add flour, salt and baking powder sifted together, alternately with the milk.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 2 greased layer cake pans in a moderately hot oven, 350° to 375° and put together as directed.

title: low-fat honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine ingredients as listed.
Use on anything you'd put a dressing on.

title: coconut crunch
directions: Mix flour, sugar, oleo and coconut.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° and keep stirring while baking crunch until light brown.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Beat the butter until soft and fluffy.
Gradually add the sugar, beating well after each addition.
Continue beating until smooth.
Beat the eggs and add them to the butter mixture.
Beat well.
Sift together the salt, baking powder and flour.
Add this gradually to the butter mixture.
Blend well after each addition. Cut the cherries, chocolate, nuts and dates into small pieces. Stir them into the batter.
Pour into a lightly greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 15 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the loaf comes out clean.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Gently fold pineapple into 1 cup of pudding.
Pour into crust. Spread remaining pudding over top.
Chill at least 4 hours. Garnish with strawberries.
Remove from fridge 10 minutes before serving.

title: ring dum diddy
directions: Bring milk to scald.
Add cheese, onion and mustard.
Stir in tomato soup.
Add flour to thicken.
Eat on crackers.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and vanilla until crumbly.
Blend in 3 tablespoons boiling water.
Add enough water (about 2 teaspoons), a teaspoon at a time, to form medium glaze of pouring consistency.
Pour quickly over top of cake.
Spread glaze evenly over top and sides.

title: canadian bacon pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pizza crust.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups cheese over crust.
Spoon pizza sauce over cheese.
Top with bacon, pineapple and onions.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until crust is brown and cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: clam fritters
directions: Wash and open clams.
Drain clams and reserve 1/3 cup liquid. Split clams and discard dark stomach contents.
Put clams through food chopper; set aside.
Add baking powder, salt, pepper and nutmeg to flour and sift again.
Add clam liquor, beaten eggs and milk and beat until smooth.
Fold in melted butter and chopped clams.
Drop by tablespoons into deep fat heated to 375°.
Fry until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with lemon wedges.

title: "lakeville lake cioppino"(from sorrento, italy)
directions: Cut fish into large pieces.
Scrub clams; remove shells from shrimp.
Heat oil in 3 or 4-quart casserole with a cover.
Add onions, garlic and chopped tomatoes.
Saute 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup wine and simmer 10 minutes.
Add fish and 1/2 bottle wine.
Add Italian seasoning, basil and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Fish will break up and thicken soup.
If too thick, add rest of bottle of wine.
If too thin, add 1 tablespoon tomato paste.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Make double recipe graham cracker crust (holding back 1 cup). Bake in large cake pan.
Blend cream cheese with sugar; add whipped cream or Dream Whip (Dream Whip cuts calories, but adds sweetness). Pour into prepared crust.
Sprinkle with the reserved crumbs and chill for several hours or overnight.
Serves 16.
Can be halved easily; fits regular pie tin.

title: baked beans
directions: Boil salt pork, cut in small pieces.
Mix the beans and put in a 9-inch square Pyrex dish.
Pour syrup or molasses over them. Pour salt pork on top.
Pour the water over all.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, margarine, vanilla and salt for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add soda, stir quickly. Pour over corn and mix well.
Place in 2 flat large pans.
Place pans in a 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir 3 or 4 times.
When cold, store in tightly closed containers.

title: klushki noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Grease casserole with butter, 9 x 13-inch.
Mix noodles, cottage cheese and sour cream. Put in casserole.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top and bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and return to oven for about 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: In a food processor bowl or blender, combine all ingredients. Cover; blend for 30 seconds.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit in bowl.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl and blend well. Pour over fruit and toss to coat.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates. Makes 5 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix crumbs; add broth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: tanabour(armenian yogurt soup)
directions: Add 1 can of water to the soup.
Cook the barley in the soup according to directions on the barley box.
Just before serving, stir the yogurt into the barley/soup mixture.
Separately melt the butter and add garlic (or garlic powder) to taste.
Place on the table in a separate bowl.
People may add the garlic butter to the soup according to their taste.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Pour on top and chill until set.

title: italian beef in the crock-pot
directions: Place meat, bouillon cubes, garlic salt and Italian dressing in crock-pot.
Add enough water to cover beef.
Cook on low for 8 hours.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar in 1 bowl.
In another bowl, beat egg.
Add buttermilk, Wesson oil and vanilla.
Stir and add liquid ingredients to dry.
Stir, leaving entire ingredients slightly lumpy.
Bake on hot griddle (greased) until bubbles form.
Turn once and bake other side or place on waffle iron until lightly browned.

title: beef 'n bean enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare ground beef and taco seasoning mix as directed on packet for taco filling.
Stir in beans and olives. Simmer over medium heat until hot, stirring occasionally.

title: party mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt butter and sauce and pour over. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Drain on newspaper.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Stir in blueberry pie filling.
Chill until set.
Combine sour cream and powdered sugar.
Spread on top.

title: green beans with mushroom sauce
directions: Place green beans in casserole.
Pour 1 can mushroom soup over beans.
Cover with canned onions.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, cutting cherries in half and draining fruit cocktail and pineapple before mixing.
Place in pie shells.
Let set for at least an hour or until chilled.

title: thirst quencher
directions: Blend milk, pineapple juice, orange peel and sections, banana slices, honey and almond extract in blender until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch square baking pan.
Partially freeze (about 45 minutes).
Spoon into chilled glasses.
Serves 4.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package and set aside.
Bake cake as directed.
Take 1/2 of cake and crumble in bottom of punch bowl.
Layer 1/2 of pudding mix, then 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 cherry pie filling, 1/2 Cool Whip and 1/2 nuts.
Repeat 2nd layer the same as before.
Easy to make.
Makes a good big dessert.

title: hawaiian flakies
directions: Mix cornflakes, coconut and nuts.
Mix butter and vanilla and drizzle over flake mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add salt and sugar and stir into flake mixture.
Put into pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: festive potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on lettuce on a nice platter.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients except for bread crumbs and butter.
Add milk to moisten.
Put bread crumbs on top and pour butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: roasted turkey breast
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place breast in lightly oiled nonstick or ovenproof dish.
Rub skin of turkey with few drops olive oil; season with salt and pepper.
Place in oven; cook until skin begins to brown, about 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 325°.

title: knoephla soup
directions: Saute margarine, potatoes and onions.
In a kettle, boil water and chicken soup base.
To make Knoephla, mix together flour, eggs and milk or water to form dough.
Season dough with onion flakes; knead well.
Roll into a rope and cut into small pieces; drop into boiling water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Then add 3 cups milk, the sauteed potatoes and onions from before.
Add 2 cups cream.
Season with crushed parsley flakes and pepper.
Simmer.
Do not boil until potatoes are soft.
EAT!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken, eggs and celery as for salad.
Mix all the ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Top with crumbs.
Cook in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: coffee eggnog
directions: Add sugar to boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Let come to a boil.
Remove from heat; add coffee and stir well.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Let drip through 2 thicknesses of wet cheesecloth in a strainer.
Let cool.
Beat egg yolks; stir in coffee syrup slowly.
Add milk and blend well.
Fold in well beaten egg whites. Pour into punch bowl.
Serve in punch cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serves 40.

title: curry dip
directions: Serve as a dip for crisp vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, etc.).

title: nora's tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix and put into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raisin cake
directions: In saucepan, cover raisins with water and boil about 10 minutes.
Take off stove and cool.
Cream together eggs, sugar and margarine.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add to wet ingredients and add raisins.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Boil the macaroni and vegetables together until almost done. Mix milk, margarine, cheese and hamburger in with the well drained macaroni and vegetables.
Stir until cheese melts. Put in casserole dish. Can be baked at 350° until done or pop in the microwave.

title: mazetti
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Boil noodles 20 minutes and drain. Spread in order, in layers, in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.
Serves 6.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into punch bowl. Add ice.

title: spice cookies(low cholesterol)
directions: Stir flour, soda and spices; set aside.
In large bowl, beat margarine, sugar and egg whites.
Add flour mix and beat until combined.
Mix in Oat Bran cereal.
Drop by level measuring tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 9 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion (drain some liquid).
Season with salt, pepper and margarine.
Mix squash with egg, cream of mushroom soup and grated cheese.
Crush one layer of potato chips in bottom of casserole.
Put mixture in casserole dish.
Cover with foil until hot and bubbly at 350°.
Take out of oven and place a layer of the French fried onions on top.
Put back in oven to brown the onions.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients into bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle
sugar on top of that, then sprinkle bacon on. Liberally
sprinkle
on
Parmesan
cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix together before serving.

title: tripe
directions: Wash tripe thoroughly and trim away fat pockets.
Slice into even pieces about 1-inch long and 1/2-inch wide.
Boil in salted water about 1 hour; drain and set aside.
In saucepan, saute onion, pepper, celery and spices.
Add tomato paste and water. Cook until paste is evenly distributed and smooth.
Add tomatoes and cook 20 minutes over medium heat.
Add tripe and cook 30 to 45 minutes longer, until tripe is thoroughly mixed with sauce.
Serve hot with plenty or bread and hot crushed pepper.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice in a little bit of oil until slightly toasted. Remove from pan.
Next, saute onions and celery in the same pan; add more oil, if needed.
Add rice and remaining ingredients and water.
Cover and cook about 30 minutes, until rice is soft (per recipe on box of rice).

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until forms a ball.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Remove from heat and beat until creamy. Pour in lightly greased pan and cool.

title: pasta fa sou
directions: Break spaghetti into thirds and cook; drain.
In 1 tablespoon oil cook the onion until light brown.
Add the sauce, beans, salt, pepper and parsley.
Let simmer 3 minutes.
Add sauce to spaghetti and simmer 3 to 5 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; add fruit and nuts. Pour half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Lightly grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch. Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Place about 2-inches apart in pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown. Remove from pan. Serve warm. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: broccoli and cheese pastries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Steam broccoli florets and set aside to cool.
In a medium bowl, mix the cheese, green onion, dill weed and nutmeg.
Unfold crusts.
Cut each crust in half, creating 4 half circles.
Add broccoli to medium bowl and toss ingredients. Mound 1/4 of the filling on each half pastry; press filling to compact it.
Fold the pastry closed and seal edges with a fork. Pierce pastry with the tines of a fork several times.
Place pastries on a large baking sheet; brush generously with glaze. Bake pastries for 22 minutes, until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4.
Reheat well in a microwave.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Wash okra and drain.
Remove tips and stem ends.
Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Add okra and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, 2 eggs, 2 tablespoons of butter, sugar, 2 tablespoons of flour and grated peel until creamy.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.

title: yum yum cake
directions: *Fruit mixture: Make a fruit mixture by mixing crushed pineapple, coconut, and mandarin oranges.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender, let cool.
Remove meat from bone and cut into pieces.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover the chicken with chicken soup, then cover with biscuits.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are done or brown.

title: super gingersnap molasses cookies
directions: Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Press down and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown around edges.

title: brownies
directions: In pan, melt butter and chocolate. Place in bowl and add eggs, sugar and the rest of the ingredients; mix until smooth. Pour into greased 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat oil, sugar and egg together.
Add zucchini and vanilla to mixture and mix well.
Add all dry ingredients and nuts, then blend well.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: arkansas cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Add nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is still hot, poke holes in cake with fork.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on top while still hot.
Spread crushed pineapple and juice on top.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour drained fruit cocktail in large bowl.
Drain and cut up sliced peaches.
Add pineapple tidbits (juice and fruit).
Stir in vanilla pudding (dry) and Tang (dry).
Mix well.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Can add sliced bananas just before serving.

title: rigatoni salad
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar, oil, turmeric and water until sugar dissolves.
Add pimento, pepper, cauliflower, onion, mushrooms and artichokes.
Cook rigatoni 19 minutes; drain.
Mix all together. Marinate 24 hours.
Can add diced Colby cheese before serving.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; make cornbread mix. Add peas,
1/2 of grated cheese and creamed corn.
Mix thoroughly; pour over ground beef and mix.
Add rest of grated cheese over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad bake
directions: Mix and add dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Cover bottom of casserole with chow mein noodles. Pour in mixture. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Add noodles to top and let brown.

title: tuna fish dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover; blend until smooth, stopping to stir with spatula every few minutes until all ingredients are blended well.

title: nine day pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in brine (2 cups salt to 1 gallon water).
Soak for 3 days.
Drain.
Put fresh water on each day for the next 7 days.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine beef, salt, pepper, steak sauce, bread crumbs, and egg in large bowl; blend well.
Gently shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet on moderate heat.
Brown meatballs on all sides.
Reduce heat to low; cook 10 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove meatballs; set aside.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons butter to drippings in skillet.
Raise heat to moderate; add mushrooms.
Saute until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour, catsup and Worcestershire.
Add broth and onion soup mix; stir constantly until thickened.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 2 minutes.
Add meatballs; heat through.
Stir in sour cream; heat through but do not boil.
Open potatoes.
Fluff insides with fork.
Spoon stroganoff mixture over each potato. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve hot.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix flour, yeast and sugar.
Add water, oil and beaten egg. Fill each muffin tin about 1/2 full. Bake at 450 degrees until brown.

title: fresh shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Heat soup to boiling point and add cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix well; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 4-cup mold.
(A fish shaped mold is nice.) Chill for at least 2 hours and serve with crackers.

title: marbled pudding
directions: Pour milk into small bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat on low speed until well blended 1 or 2 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes. Fold whipped topping into pudding for a marbled effect. Garnish with additional topping.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, beating until smooth.
Add vanilla and salt; beat until thoroughly blended.
Stir in coconut and pecans.

title: aunt joy's quick fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Easy but very good.

title: becky's day ahead banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with milk until blended.
Add sour cream and condensed milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
In large bowl or 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish, layer wafers and sliced bananas.
Add pudding. Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
If desired, top with additional whipped topping.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix biscuit mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms. Beat 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix butter and garlic powder.
Brush over hot biscuits.

title: steak marinade
directions: Chop garlic
and
let
stand
in
oil
for
30 minutes. Remove garlic and add soy sauce and Worcestershire;
let stand for 2 hours.
After you marinate, you can barbecue or grill.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Let butter, peanut butter, eggs and buttermilk warm to room temperature for easy mixing (butter should be very soft).
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Combine room temperature ingredients with remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat on slow speed of an electric mixer for 30 seconds, then at medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping sides of bowl.

title: candy snack mix
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl with raisins on top. Sprinkle generously with cinnamon and mix all ingredients together well. Store in an airtight container. Makes approximately 3 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle dry soup in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place, uncooked rice, over soup, then arrange chicken over rice.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients by hand until well mixed, then remaining ingredients.
Mix well (2 minutes with electric mixer). Pour in a Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Test with cake tester for doneness.
Cool on rack 20 minutes.
Remove from pan, cool, then ice with Betty Crocker chocolate icing.

title: can't fail quiche
directions: Stir cornstarch into milk until dissolved.
Add eggs and mayonnaise; mix well.
Add spinach and onions.
Stir in cheese. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until center is puffed and lightly browned.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix until well blended.
Add more dry milk if too sticky.
Use it like play dough, then eat it!

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Cook soup bone in water for 3 hours.
Remove bone.
Add salt, pepper, bouillon or chicken stock, rice and parsley.
Cook 25 minutes or until rice is done. Serve hot.

title: father's coffee cake
directions: Cook together for 8 minutes the 1 cup sugar, cold coffee and cocoa.
While this is cooling, cream butter, 1 cup sugar and eggs. Then add 1 cup cold coffee.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder and add to other ingredients.
Stir in the cool, cooked mixture.
Bake in loaf pan at 375° until done.
(Do not add more flour.)

title: applesauce cake
directions: Dissolve soda in applesauce.

title: raspberry vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir vigorously or put into a jar and shake well.
Serve over mixed greens.

title: red hot sauce
directions: Mix in blender on grate until well mixed.
Bring vinegar to preboil.
Add to blender until desired thickness.
Turn blender to liquify.
Blend and add hot vinegar until desired thickness.

title: potato leek soup
directions: In a large soup pot, combine potatoes, leeks, stock, water and butter.
Bring to a boil, turn down heat and let simmer for about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Taste for seasoning and add salt and pepper if needed.
Mash some of the potatoes into the soup to thicken slightly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Layer 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1/2 bag coconut.
Mix devil's food cake mix with pudding by directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Next, mix 1 stick butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar on the stove.
Pour over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches, reserve juice.
In an 8 x 8-inch square pan, oil lightly and dust with 1/4 cup Jiffy baking mix.
Arrange peaches on Jiffy baking mix.
In small bowl, combine egg, peach juice and cake mix.
Mix well and pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: blueberry roll
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to drained and cleaned berries.
Grease jelly roll pan (16 x 10 x 1/4-inches).
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar, flour, baking powder and salt, then add 6 tablespoons butter; flake.
Add egg and milk and beat.
Roll out onto jelly roll pan; spread.
Spread 2 tablespoons butter and berries over roll; seal.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: grandma's custard pie
directions: Prepare favorite pastry for double crust 9-inch pie*.
To make filling:
Mix together dry ingredients; toss with fruit and lemon juice, if used.
Turn into pastry lined pie plate.
Dot with margarine.
Make several slits in top crust.
Cover pie with pastry; seal and flute edge.
Bake as directed or until crust is browned.

title: apple dumplings
directions: To make sauce, combine sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cook 5 minutes and add butter.
Pare and core apples.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder; cut in shortening.
Add milk all at once and stir just until flour is moistened.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut six 5-inch squares.
Place one apple on each square; sprinkle generously with additional sugar and spices.
Dot with butter; fold corners up over apple and pinch edges.
Place 1-inch apart in greased baking pan.
Pour over sauce and bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve warm with cream.
You'll get raves!

title: spinach pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a buttered casserole dish or ring mold.
Place dish in a hot water bath and bake at 375° until firm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix pepperoni, egg, cheese and oregano in bowl.
Roll 2 crescent rolls to form rectangle.
Spread ingredients on crescent rolls.
Roll up and slice 1/2-inch thick. Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Delicious!!

title: chicken noodle casserole royale
directions: Bake chicken breast halves at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (or until done).
Remove chicken from bones and discard skin.
Cut meat into bite-size pieces (1 1/2 to 2 cups of chicken).
Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole, soup, sour cream and thyme.
Stir in cooked noodles, diced pimento and chicken meat.
Top with bread crumbs combined with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until blended.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture along with buttermilk and mashed bananas. Mix just until batter is smooth and well blended.
Stir in 1/4 cup of the nuts.
Spread in a buttered 9-inch square cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with favorite chocolate frosting and sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Makes 1 (9-inch) cake.

title: lime dessert
directions: Beat 4 minutes.
Pour over cake and top with Cool Whip and freeze.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix ingredients and spread over 1st layer.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter cookies
